557
00:34:00,560 --> 00:34:03,594
- Thank you.
- I got some camouflage jackets here.

558
00:34:03,664 --> 00:34:06,664
- I suggest you both put them on.
- Camouflage jackets?

559
00:34:06,737 --> 00:34:09,736
Yes, sir. We'll be riding
pretty close to the fence line.

560
00:34:09,808 --> 00:34:11,880
The Cubans see
an officer wearing white...

561
00:34:11,952 --> 00:34:14,408
they think it might be someone
they want to take a shot at.

562
00:34:16,145 --> 00:34:18,511
Good call, Sam.

563
00:34:22,898 --> 00:34:25,418
We'll just hop on the ferry.
We'll be there in no time.

564
00:34:25,490 --> 00:34:27,977
- Wait. We gotta take a boat?
- Yes, sir.

565
00:34:28,049 --> 00:34:31,530
- To get to the other side of the bay.
- Nobody said anything about a boat.

566
00:34:31,602 --> 00:34:34,285
- Is there a problem, sir?
- No, no problem.

567
00:34:34,354 --> 00:34:36,045
Just not crazy about boats.

568
00:34:36,114 --> 00:34:40,207
Jesus Christ, Kaffee,
you're in the Navy, for crying out loud.

569
00:34:40,276 --> 00:34:43,691
- Nobody likes her very much.
- Yes, sir!

570
00:34:56,340 --> 00:34:58,829
Nathan Jessup. Come on in.

571
00:34:58,901 --> 00:35:02,763
Thank you, sir. Daniel Kaffee.
I'm the attorney for Dawson and Downey.

572
00:35:02,837 --> 00:35:05,106
This is
Lieutenant Commander Joanne Galloway.

573
00:35:05,173 --> 00:35:08,240
- Pleasure meeting you, Commander.
- Observing and evaluating, sir.

574
00:35:08,310 --> 00:35:10,164
Lieutenant Sam Weinberg.
He'll be assisting.

575
00:35:10,230 --> 00:35:12,847
- Sir.
- This is my X.O., Colonel Markinson...

576
00:35:12,917 --> 00:35:14,860
and platoon leader Lieutenant Kendrick.

577
00:35:14,934 --> 00:35:17,324
I've asked them to join us.
Sit down, please.

578
00:35:17,399 --> 00:35:19,765
- Lieutenant Kaffee.
- Colonel Markinson.

579
00:35:19,831 --> 00:35:22,220
I had the pleasure
of meeting your father once.

580
00:35:22,295 --> 00:35:24,269
I was a teenager.
He spoke at my high school.

581
00:35:25,239 --> 00:35:26,384
Lionel Kaffee?

582
00:35:27,190 --> 00:35:29,079
- Yes, sir.
- Well, what do you know?

583
00:35:29,143 --> 00:35:33,550
John, this man's dad once made a lot of
enemies down in your neck of the woods.

584
00:35:33,623 --> 00:35:37,236
Jefferson v. Madison County
School District.

585
00:35:37,304 --> 00:35:41,461
Folks down there said a black girl
couldn't go to an all-white school.

586
00:35:41,528 --> 00:35:45,303
Lionel Kaffee said,
'Well, we'll just see about that.'

587
00:35:45,368 --> 00:35:47,823
How the hell is your dad, Danny?

588
00:35:47,896 --> 00:35:50,197
He passed away seven years ago, sir.

589
00:35:51,865 --> 00:35:54,615
Don't I feel like the fuckin' asshole.

590
00:35:54,682 --> 00:35:55,958
Not at all.

591
00:35:57,145 --> 00:35:59,153
Well, what can we do for you, Danny?

592
00:35:59,226 --> 00:36:01,081
Uh, not much, sir.

593
00:36:02,522 --> 00:36:06,265
This is really a formality
more than anything else.

594
00:36:07,291 --> 00:36:10,073
JAG Corps insists that we interview
all the relevant witnesses.

595
00:36:10,138 --> 00:36:12,026
The JAG Corps can be demanding
that way.

596
00:36:13,692 --> 00:36:16,375
John will take you out
and show you what you want to see.

597
00:36:16,443 --> 00:36:18,417
After that we can all
hook up for lunch.

598
00:36:18,491 --> 00:36:21,591
- How does that sound? Good.
- Fine, sir.

599
00:36:29,372 --> 00:36:31,708
I understand you had a meeting
with your men that afternoon.

600
00:36:31,773 --> 00:36:34,009
- Yes, I did.
- What did you guys talk about?

601
00:36:34,076 --> 00:36:36,346
I told the men
that we had an informer among us...

602
00:36:36,413 --> 00:36:39,282
and that despite any desire
they might have to seek retribution...

603
00:36:39,357 --> 00:36:42,706
Private Santiago
was not to be harmed in anyway.

604
00:36:42,780 --> 00:36:45,945
- What time was that meeting?
- 1600.

605
00:36:46,013 --> 00:36:48,762
That's 4:00.

606
00:37:38,018 --> 00:37:40,439
Sam, we should make sure
somebody gets this to his parents.

607
00:37:40,514 --> 00:37:43,548
- We don't need it anymore.
- Right.

608
00:37:44,771 --> 00:37:46,942
Lieutenant Kendrick,
may I call you John?

609
00:37:47,011 --> 00:37:48,985
No, you may not.

610
00:37:49,059 --> 00:37:51,100
Have I done something to offend you?

611
00:37:51,172 --> 00:37:53,179
No, I like all you Navy boys.

612
00:37:53,252 --> 00:37:57,146
Every time we gotta go someplace to
fight, you fellas always give us a ride.

613
00:37:58,467 --> 00:38:01,762
Lieutenant Kendrick,
do you think Santiago was murdered?

614
00:38:01,828 --> 00:38:04,578
Commander, I believe in God
and His Son Jesus Christ.

615
00:38:04,644 --> 00:38:06,554
And because I do, I can say this:

616
00:38:06,629 --> 00:38:10,207
Private Santiago is dead,
and that is a tragedy.

617
00:38:10,277 --> 00:38:12,448
But he is dead
because he had no code.

618
00:38:12,516 --> 00:38:16,640
He is dead because he had no honor,
and God was watching.

619
00:38:19,013 --> 00:38:20,704
How do you feel about that theory?

620
00:38:20,774 --> 00:38:22,913
Sounds good. Let's move on.

621
00:38:22,982 --> 00:38:24,891
Are you planning
on doing any investigating...

622
00:38:24,966 --> 00:38:26,821
or are you just gonna take
the guided tour?

623
00:38:28,390 --> 00:38:31,074
I'm pacing myself.

624
00:38:31,878 --> 00:38:33,536
They were running around
for three hours...

625
00:38:33,606 --> 00:38:36,422
looking for anything white
they could wave in the air.

626
00:38:36,487 --> 00:38:39,650
Some of these people surrendered
to a crew from CNN.

627
00:38:40,679 --> 00:38:45,731
Well, walk softly and carry
an armored tank division, I always say.

628
00:38:47,144 --> 00:38:50,243
- That was delicious. Thank you.
- My pleasure, sir.

629
00:38:50,312 --> 00:38:54,948
Colonel, I do have to ask you a couple
of questions about September 6.

630
00:38:55,016 --> 00:38:56,542
Shoot.

631
00:38:56,616 --> 00:38:59,105
On the morning of the sixth,
you were contacted by an N.I.S. agent...

632
00:38:59,178 --> 00:39:02,472
who said that Santiago tipped him off
to an illegal fence line shooting.

633
00:39:02,537 --> 00:39:04,642
- Yes.
- Santiago would reveal the person...

634
00:39:04,713 --> 00:39:07,397
- in exchange for a transfer.
- Yes.

635
00:39:10,377 --> 00:39:13,061
If you feel there are any details
that I'm missing...

636
00:39:13,130 --> 00:39:16,229
you should feel free to speak up.

637
00:39:18,699 --> 00:39:20,074
Thank you.

638
00:39:23,499 --> 00:39:26,182
Now, at this point you called
Lieutenant Colonel Markinson...

639
00:39:26,250 --> 00:39:28,488
and Lieutenant Kendrick
into your office.

640
00:39:28,555 --> 00:39:30,180
- Is that right?
- Yes.

641
00:39:30,251 --> 00:39:31,364
What happened?

642
00:39:31,435 --> 00:39:37,000
We agreed that, for his own safety,
Santiago should be transferred off base.

643
00:39:37,068 --> 00:39:40,930
Santiago was set to be transferred.

644
00:39:41,004 --> 00:39:43,492
On the first available flight
to the States...

645
00:39:43,564 --> 00:39:45,604
0600 the next morning.

646
00:39:45,677 --> 00:39:49,606
Five hours too late,
as it turned out.

647
00:39:50,829 --> 00:39:52,203
Yeah.

648
00:39:53,709 --> 00:39:55,979
All right. That's all I have.
Thanks very much for your time.

649
00:39:56,045 --> 00:39:59,210
Corporal's waiting with the Jeep.
He'll take you back to the flight line.

650
00:39:59,278 --> 00:40:01,220
- Thank you, sir.
- Wait. I've got some questions.

651
00:40:01,294 --> 00:40:02,855
- No, you don't.
- Yes, I do.

652
00:40:02,925 --> 00:40:05,796
- No, you don't.
- On the morning that Santiago died...

653
00:40:05,870 --> 00:40:09,318
did you meet with Dr. Stone
between 3:00 and 5:00?

654
00:40:09,390 --> 00:40:13,252
Of course I met with the doctor.
One of my men was dead.

655
00:40:13,326 --> 00:40:15,749
See? The man was dead. Let's go.

656
00:40:15,823 --> 00:40:19,337
I'm just wondering if you’ve ever heard
the term 'Code Red.'

657
00:40:20,624 --> 00:40:22,249
I've heard the term, yes.

658
00:40:22,319 --> 00:40:25,188
This past February,
you received a cautionary memo...

659
00:40:25,263 --> 00:40:27,468
from the commander-in-chief
of the Atlantic fleet...

660
00:40:27,536 --> 00:40:29,391
warning that the practice
of enlisted men...

661
00:40:29,456 --> 00:40:32,490
disciplining their own
wasn't to be condoned by officers.

662
00:40:32,561 --> 00:40:34,983
Well, I submit to you
that whoever wrote that memo...

663
00:40:35,057 --> 00:40:36,912
has never faced the working end...

664
00:40:36,977 --> 00:40:40,871
of a Soviet-made
Cuban AK-47 assault rifle.

665
00:40:40,945 --> 00:40:44,491
However, the directive
having come from the commander...

666
00:40:44,561 --> 00:40:46,601
I gave it its due attention.

667
00:40:46,674 --> 00:40:49,130
- What is your point, Jo?
- She has no point.

668
00:40:49,201 --> 00:40:51,057
She often has no point.
It's part of her charm.

669
00:40:51,122 --> 00:40:55,911
- We're out of here. Thank you.
- I think Code Reds still go on here.

670
00:40:55,986 --> 00:41:00,078
- Do Code Reds still happen here?
-Jo, he doesn't need to answer that.

671
00:41:00,147 --> 00:41:01,641
- Yes, he does.
- No, he really doesn't.

672
00:41:01,715 --> 00:41:03,689
Yeah, he really does.

673
00:41:08,243 --> 00:41:10,383
You know, it just hit me.

674
00:41:11,412 --> 00:41:13,267
She outranks you, Danny.

675
00:41:13,332 --> 00:41:16,049
- Yes, sir.
- I want to tell you something.

676
00:41:16,116 --> 00:41:18,538
And listen up,
'cause I really mean this.

677
00:41:18,611 --> 00:41:21,230
You're the luckiest man
in the world.

678
00:41:21,300 --> 00:41:25,424
There is nothing on this earth sexier--
believe me, gentlemen--

679
00:41:25,492 --> 00:41:28,363
than a woman that
you have to salute in the morning.

680
00:41:29,014 --> 00:41:32,178
Promote 'em all, I say,
'cause this is true:

681
00:41:32,246 --> 00:41:35,246
If you haven't gotten a blowjob
from a superior officer...

682
00:41:35,318 --> 00:41:39,595
well, you’re just letting
the best in life pass you by.

683
00:41:40,726 --> 00:41:43,279
Colonel, the practice of Code Reds
is still condoned by officers--

684
00:41:43,350 --> 00:41:47,606
My problem is that I'm a colonel,
so I'll go on taking cold showers...

685
00:41:47,670 --> 00:41:50,126
until they elect some gal president.

686
00:41:50,199 --> 00:41:52,566
