00:49:16,413 --> 00:49:19,348
Ooh, how can we ever thank you?

824
00:49:19,420 --> 00:49:21,875
Fellas, you hear what I just said?

825
00:49:21,948 --> 00:49:25,080
You're going home in six months.

826
00:49:25,149 --> 00:49:27,385
I'm afraid we can't do that, sir.

827
00:49:27,453 --> 00:49:30,649
- Do what?
- Make a deal, sir.

828
00:49:30,718 --> 00:49:32,125
What are you talking about?

829
00:49:32,190 --> 00:49:34,907
We did nothing wrong, sir.
We did our job...

830
00:49:34,974 --> 00:49:38,007
and if that has consequences,
then I'll accept them.

831
00:49:38,078 --> 00:49:40,380
But I won't say that I'm guilty, sir.

832
00:49:41,662 --> 00:49:45,077
Did you--
Did she put you up to this?

833
00:49:45,150 --> 00:49:48,500
- We have a code, sir.
- Oh, well, zip-a-dee-doo-dah!

834
00:49:48,574 --> 00:49:51,772
You and your code plead not guilty.
You'll be in jail the rest of your life.

835
00:49:51,840 --> 00:49:54,775
Do what I'm telling you,
you'll be home in six months.

836
00:49:56,544 --> 00:49:58,431
Do it, Harold.
Six months.

837
00:49:58,496 --> 00:50:00,918
It's nothing.
It's a hockey season.

