the psycho-babble father bullshit!

897
00:53:29,702 --> 00:53:32,963
Dawson and Downeywill have their day
in court, but with another lawyer.

898
00:53:33,029 --> 00:53:35,877
Another lawyer won’t be good enough.
They need you.

899
00:53:35,942 --> 00:53:39,358
You know how to win. You know they have
a case, and you know how to win.

900
00:53:39,431 --> 00:53:41,765
If you walk away from this now,
you've sealed their fate.

901
00:53:41,830 --> 00:53:45,060
Their fate was sealed
the moment Santiago died.

902
00:53:45,127 --> 00:53:47,647
- Do you believe they have a case?
- You and Dawson.

903
00:53:47,719 --> 00:53:49,694
You both live
in the same dream world.

904
00:53:49,767 --> 00:53:51,621
It doesn't matter what I believe.

905
00:53:51,686 --> 00:53:53,727
It only matters what I can prove.

906
00:53:53,799 --> 00:53:56,614
So, please, don't tell me
what I know and don't know!

907
00:53:56,680 --> 00:53:58,370
I know the law!

908
00:54:03,144 --> 00:54:04,999
You know nothing about the law.

909
00:54:05,064 --> 00:54:07,170
You're a used car salesman, Daniel.

910
00:54:07,241 --> 00:54:09,629
You're an ambulance chaser
with a rank.

911
00:54:09,704 --> 00:54:12,672
You're nothing. Live with that.

912
00:54:18,953 --> 00:54:20,808
So I told Duncan...

913
00:54:20,873 --> 00:54:24,867
'If you want to take this to court
I'm gonna file nine discovery motions...

914
00:54:24,938 --> 00:54:28,101
and you're gonna spend a year
going blind on paperwork...

915
00:54:28,170 --> 00:54:31,520
because a 90-year-old man
misread the Delaware insurance code.'

916
00:54:31,595 --> 00:54:33,700
- So what happened?
- He calls back 15 minutes later.

917
00:54:33,771 --> 00:54:35,625
He says, ' Let's make a deal.'

918
00:55:20,878 --> 00:55:22,253
All rise.

919
00:55:29,456 --> 00:55:30,503
Where are we?

920
00:55:32,112 --> 00:55:35,527
Docket number 411275VR-5.

921
00:55:35,600 --> 00:55:38,503
The United States v.
Lance Corporal Harold W. Dawson...

922
00:55:38,577 --> 00:55:40,518
and Private First Class Louden Downey.

923
00:55:40,592 --> 00:55:43,592
The accused are charged with murder,
conspiracy to commit murder...

924
00:55:43,664 --> 00:55:46,121
and conduct unbecoming
a United States Marine.

925
00:55:46,194 --> 00:55:48,298
Does the defense wish to enter a plea?

926
00:55:50,001 --> 00:55:51,377
Yeah.

927
00:55:54,929 --> 00:55:56,271
They're not guilty.

928
00:55:59,314 --> 00:56:01,801
Enter a plea of not guilty
for the accused.

929
00:56:01,874 --> 00:56:05,006
We'll adjourn until 1000,
three weeks from today...

930
00:56:05,074 --> 00:56:07,890
at which time this general
court-martial will reconvene.

931
00:56:23,797 --> 00:56:27,113
Why does a lieutenant junior grade
with ninth months' experience...

932
00:56:27,189 --> 00:56:30,418
and a track record for plea bargaining
get assigned a murder case?

933
00:56:33,141 --> 00:56:36,011
Would it be so that it never sees
the inside of a courtroom?

934
00:56:38,517 --> 00:56:40,371
We'll work out of my apartment
every night, 7:00.

935
00:56:40,436 --> 00:56:44,878
Jo, pick up a carton of legal pads, half
a dozen boxes of red and black pens.

936
00:56:44,950 --> 00:56:48,049
Sam, get a couple of desk lamps.
I need a preliminary medical profile.

937
00:56:48,118 --> 00:56:52,373
Jo, we need all proficiency and conduct
reports on Dawson, Downey and Santiago.

938
00:56:52,439 --> 00:56:54,543
The only thing I have to eat
is Yoo-hoo and Cocoa Puffs...

939
00:56:54,614 --> 00:56:56,469
so if you want anything else,
bring it with you.

940
00:56:56,534 --> 00:56:58,608
- Okay?
- Yeah.

941
00:57:04,439 --> 00:57:06,741
So this is what
a courtroom looks like.

942
00:57:16,792 --> 00:57:19,214
Were you able to speak
to your friend at the N.I.S.?

943
00:57:20,249 --> 00:57:23,381
Yeah. She said if Markinson
doesn't want to be found...

944
00:57:23,449 --> 00:57:25,271
we're not gonna find him.

945
00:57:25,337 --> 00:57:28,153
She said I could be Markinson,
and you wouldn't know it.

946
00:57:29,657 --> 00:57:31,632
Are you Markinson?

947
00:57:33,817 --> 00:57:35,640
I'm not Markinson.

948
00:57:36,698 --> 00:57:38,771
That's two down.

949
00:57:40,507 --> 00:57:41,652
What?

950
00:57:43,739 --> 00:57:46,903
I'm just wondering,
now that Joanne’s on this--

951
00:57:46,971 --> 00:57:49,392
I'm just wondering
if you still need me.

952
00:57:49,466 --> 00:57:52,150
- They were following orders.
- An illegal order.

953
00:57:52,219 --> 00:57:54,358
Do you think they knew
it was an illegal order?

954
00:57:54,427 --> 00:57:57,624
It doesn't matter what they knew.
Any decent person would have refused--

955
00:57:57,692 --> 00:57:59,864
They're not permitted
to question orders.

956
00:57:59,932 --> 00:58:02,834
Then what's the secret? Huh?
What are the magic words?

957
00:58:02,908 --> 00:58:04,434
I give orders every day--

958
00:58:04,508 --> 00:58:06,364
We have softball games
and marching bands.

959
00:58:06,429 --> 00:58:10,455
They work at a place where you have to
wear camouflage or you might get shot!

960
00:58:17,886 --> 00:58:19,860
I need you.

961
00:58:19,933 --> 00:58:24,668
You're better at research than I am,
and you know how to prepare a witness.

962
00:58:29,854 --> 00:58:32,854
I've got medical reports
and Chinese food. I say we eat first.

963
00:58:40,063 --> 00:58:41,078
What?

964
00:58:43,200 --> 00:58:45,055
You got any kung pao chicken?

965
00:58:48,287 --> 00:58:51,670
This is our defense-- intent. No one
can prove there was poison on the rag.

966
00:58:51,744 --> 00:58:54,494
Code Red-- they're common
and accepted in Guantanamo Bay.

967
00:58:54,561 --> 00:58:58,751
The order-- A: Kendrick gave it,
B: They had to follow it.

968
00:58:58,817 --> 00:59:00,857
- That's it.
- What about motive?

969
00:59:00,929 --> 00:59:02,871
We're a little weak on motive.
They had one.

970
00:59:02,945 --> 00:59:05,018
- That doesn't mean they're guilty.
- Relax.

971
00:59:05,090 --> 00:59:07,359
We'll deal with the fence line shooting
when it comes up.

972
00:59:07,426 --> 00:59:10,459
Let's start with intent. I don't
want to know what made Santiago die.

973
00:59:10,529 --> 00:59:13,346
I just want to show it could've been
something other than poison.

974
00:59:13,411 --> 00:59:16,826
Jo, talk to doctors. Find out everything
there is to know about lactic acidosis.

975
00:59:16,898 --> 00:59:20,063
This is Lieutenant Commander Galloway
with the JAG Corps in Washington.

976
00:59:20,131 --> 00:59:23,229
I've been trying to track down
a Lieutenant Colonel Matthew Markinson.

977
00:59:23,298 --> 00:59:26,015
Doctor, was there any sign
of external damage?

978
00:59:26,082 --> 00:59:30,394
No scrapes? No cuts?
Bruises? Broken bones?

979
00:59:30,468 --> 00:59:34,658
- Was there any sign of violence?
- You mean, other than the dead body?

980
00:59:34,723 --> 00:59:37,375
Shit, I walk into that
every goddamn time.

981
00:59:37,444 --> 00:59:41,884
He ordered me and Lance Corporal Dawson
to give Willie a Code Red.

982
00:59:41,956 --> 00:59:44,095
Answers still have to come
much faster.

983
00:59:44,164 --> 00:59:46,171
This Iowa farm boy thing
will play for a while...

984
00:59:46,244 --> 00:59:48,547
but in the end, it sounds
like he's searching for the truth.

985
00:59:48,613 --> 00:59:50,785
He's right. From now on,
Willie is Private Santiago.

986
00:59:50,854 --> 00:59:53,090
You start calling him Willie,
and all of a sudden he's a person...

987
00:59:53,157 --> 00:59:55,296
who's got a mother
who's gonna miss him, okay?

988
00:59:55,366 --> 00:59:57,221
They drew the court members
this afternoon.

989
00:59:57,286 --> 00:59:59,490
Seven men, two women,
five Navy, four Marines.

990
00:59:59,558 --> 01:00:01,980
All officers with line experience.
Neither of the women have children.

991
01:00:02,053 --> 01:00:04,257
That's a bad break.
There’s nothing we can do.

992
01:00:04,325 --> 01:00:06,978
My father always said a jury trial
is not just about the law.

993
01:00:07,048 --> 01:00:10,081
It's about assigning blame.
Santiago's dead, and he shouldn't be.

994
01:00:10,151 --> 01:00:12,901
These nine people are gonna insist
that someone be blamed for that.

995
01:00:12,967 --> 01:00:15,334
Ross is handing them our clients.
We're gonna hand them Kendrick.

996
01:00:15,399 --> 01:00:18,781
This is about a sales pitch.
It's gonna be won by the lawyers.

997
01:00:18,855 --> 01:00:22,020
So remember, poker faces. Don’t flinch
in front of the court members.

998
01:00:22,088 --> 01:00:25,700
Something doesn't go our way, don't hang
your head or shift in your seat.

999
01:00:25,768 --> 01:00:29,347
Whatever happens, you have to look like
it's exactly what you knew would happen.

1000
01:00:29,417 --> 01:00:33,824
- If you pass me documents--
- Do it swiftly and don't look eager.

1001
01:00:33,896 --> 01:00:37,028
Don't wear that perfume in court.
Wrecks my concentration.

1002
01:00:37,097 --> 01:00:38,471
Really?

1003
01:00:38,537 --> 01:00:40,773
I was talking to Sam.

1004
01:00:42,089 --> 01:00:43,431
What time is it?

1005
01:00:43,497 --> 01:00:45,407
It's time to go home.
Try to get some sleep.

1006
01:00:45,482 --> 01:00:47,424
- Yeah.
- Give me a ride?

1007
01:00:47,498 --> 01:00:48,872
Sure.

1008
01:00:51,722 --> 01:00:53,794
You're a good man, Charlie Brown.

1009
01:00:53,866 --> 01:00:56,255
I'll see you in court, counselor.

1010
01:01:02,732 --> 01:01:04,838
- Danny, I--
- You don't have to say it.

1011
01:01:04,909 --> 01:01:07,210
We've had our differences.
I said some things I didn't mean.

1012
01:01:07,276 --> 01:01:10,505
You said some things you didn't mean,
but you’re happy I stuck with the case.

1013
01:01:10,571 --> 01:01:14,794
And if you’ve gained a certain respect
for me over the last three weeks...

1014
01:01:14,861 --> 01:01:16,835
of course, I'm happy about that.

1015
01:01:16,908 --> 01:01:18,915
But we don't have to make
a whole big deal out of it.

1016
01:01:18,988 --> 01:01:21,161
If you like me,
I won't make you say it.

1017
01:01:21,230 --> 01:01:24,525
I was just gonna tell you
to wear matching socks tomorrow.

1018
01:01:26,317 --> 01:01:29,514
Okay. Good tip.

1019
01:01:30,318 --> 01:01:31,528
We're ready.

1020
01:01:31,597 --> 01:01:33,931
Better believe it.

1021
01:01:43,439 --> 01:01:45,294
We're gonna get creamed.

1022
01:02:13,553 --> 01:02:15,593
- Lieutenant Kaffee?
- Yes?

1023
01:02:15,665 --> 01:02:17,934
You are gonna save our son,
aren’t you?

1024
01:02:18,962 --> 01:02:20,239
I'll do my best.

1025
01:02:20,978 --> 01:02:25,451
Danny, I'd like you to meet
Ginny Miller, Louden's aunt.

1026
01:02:26,418 --> 01:02:29,265
- You're Aunt Ginny?
- Uh-huh.

1027
01:02:30,418 --> 01:02:33,451
I'm sorry. I was expecting
someone older.

1028
01:02:33,522 --> 01:02:35,181
So was I.

1029
01:02:39,092 --> 01:02:41,034
Last chance.
I'll flip you for it.

1030
01:02:41,108 --> 01:02:43,442
- All rise.
- Too late.

1031
01:02:51,604 --> 01:02:54,638
All those having business
with this general court-martial...

1032
01:02:54,709 --> 01:02:57,165
stand forward
and you shall be heard.

1033
01:02:57,238 --> 01:03:00,554
Colonel Julius Alexander Randolph
is presiding.

1034
01:03:00,629 --> 01:03:03,084
Is the government prepared
to make an opening statement?

1035
01:03:03,156 --> 01:03:04,532
Yes, sir.

1036
01:03:07,701 --> 01:03:09,675
The facts of the case are these:

1037
01:03:09,749 --> 01:03:12,433
On midnight of September 6,
the accused entered the barracks room...

1038
01:03:12,501 --> 01:03:15,350
of their platoon mate,
P.F.C. William Santiago.

1039
01:03:15,415 --> 01:03:18,383
They woke him up,
tied his arms and legs with tape...

1040
01:03:18,456 --> 01:03:20,627
and forced a rag into his throat.

1041
01:03:20,695 --> 01:03:24,142
A few minutes later, a chemical reaction
called lactic acidosis...

1042
01:03:24,215 --> 01:03:26,256
caused his lungs to begin bleeding.

1043
01:03:26,328 --> 01:03:28,182
He drowned in his own blood...

1044
01:03:28,247 --> 01:03:31,728
and was pronounced dead
at 37 minutes past midnight.

1045
01:03:31,800 --> 01:03:36,623
These are the facts of the case,
and they are undisputed.

1046
01:03:36,697 --> 01:03:40,177
That's right.
The story I’ve just told you...

1047
01:03:40,248 --> 01:03:43,663
is the exact same story you’re gonna
hear from Lance Corporal Dawson...

1048
01:03:43,736 --> 01:03:46,354
and it's the exact same story
you're gonna hear from Private Downey.

1049
01:03:46,424 --> 01:03:49,011
Furthermore, the government
will also demonstrate...

1050
01:03:49,081 --> 01:03:51,417
that the accused
soaked the rag in poison...

1051
01:03:51,482 --> 01:03:55,410
and entered Santiago's room
with motive and intent to kill.

1052
01:03:56,763 --> 01:03:58,705
Now, Lieutenant Kaffee...

1053
01:03:58,778 --> 01:04:01,745
is gonna try and pull off
a little magic act here.

1054
01:04:01,817 --> 01:04:04,207
He's gonna try a little misdirection.

1055
01:04:04,283 --> 01:04:07,861
He's gonna astonish you
with stories of rituals...

1056
01:04:07,931 --> 01:04:10,714
and dazzle you
with official-sounding terms...

1057
01:04:10,780 --> 01:04:12,634
like 'Code Red.'

1058
01:04:13,755 --> 01:04:16,854
He might even try to cut into
a few officers for you.

1059
01:04:16,924 --> 01:04:21,594
He'll have no evidence, mind you, none,
but it's gonna be entertaining.

1060
01:04:21,660 --> 01:04:25,008
And when we get to the end,
all the magic in the world...

1061
01:04:25,083 --> 01:04:27,671
will not have been able to divert
your attention from the fact...

1062
01:04:27,741 --> 01:04:33,011
that Willie Santiago is dead
and Dawson and Downey killed him.

1063
01:04:34,493 --> 01:04:37,842
These are the facts of the case,
and they are undisputed.

1064
01:04:39,581 --> 01:04:41,108
Lieutenant Kaffee.

1065
01:04:41,181 --> 01:04:43,963
There was no poison on the rag,
and there was no intent to kill.

1066
01:04:44,029 --> 01:04:48,570
Any attempt to prove otherwise is futile
'cause it just ain't true.

1067
01:04:48,639 --> 01:04:51,737
When Dawson and Downey went
into Santiago's room that night...

1068
01:04:51,806 --> 01:04:54,294
it wasn't because of vengeance
or hatred.

1069
01:04:54,367 --> 01:04:57,913
It wasn't to kill or harm, and it wasn't
because they were looking for kicks.

1070
01:04:57,983 --> 01:05:00,601
It's because it was
what they were ordered to do.

1071
01:05:01,950 --> 01:05:03,325
Let me say that again.

1072
01:05:03,391 --> 01:05:06,327
It's because it was
what they were ordered to do.

1073
01:05:07,264 --> 01:05:08,889
Out in the real world
that means nothing...

1074
01:05:08,960 --> 01:05:12,954
and here at the Washington Navy Yard
it doesn't mean a whole lot more.

1075
01:05:13,024 --> 01:05:16,820
But if you’re a Marine assigned
to Rifle Security Company Windward...

1076
01:05:16,896 --> 01:05:19,712
Guantanamo Bay, Cuba,
and you're given an order...

1077
01:05:19,777 --> 01:05:22,264
you follow it
or you pack your bags.

1078
01:05:22,336 --> 01:05:24,247
Make no mistake about it.

1079
01:05:24,321 --> 01:05:27,453
Harold Dawson and Louden Downey
are sitting before you today...

1080
01:05:27,521 --> 01:05:30,750
because they did their job.

1081
01:05:34,114 --> 01:05:36,318
Is the government ready
to call its first witness?

1082
01:05:37,410 --> 01:05:40,858
If it please the court,
the government calls Mr. R.C. McGuire.

1083
01:05:45,123 --> 01:05:47,228
Mr. McGuire, would you
raise your right hand, please?

1084
01:05:47,299 --> 01:05:49,950
Do you solemnly swear that the testimony
you give this general court-martial...

1085
01:05:50,019 --> 01:05:52,834
will be the truth, the whole truth
and nothing but the truth?

1086
01:05:52,899 --> 01:05:56,096
- I do.
- Have a seat, please, sir.

1087
01:05:56,164 --> 01:05:59,393
Would you state your full name
and occupation, for the record?

1088
01:05:59,459 --> 01:06:03,716
Robert C. McGuire, Special Agent,
Naval Investigative Service.

1089
01:06:03,781 --> 01:06:07,905
Mr. McGuire, did your office receive
a letter from P.F.C. William Santiago...

1090
01:06:07,973 --> 01:06:10,013
on 3 September of this year?

1091
01:06:10,085 --> 01:06:12,289
- We did.
- What did that letter say?

1092
01:06:12,357 --> 01:06:16,830
That a member of Santiago’s unit
had fired his weapon over the fence line.

1093
01:06:16,900 --> 01:06:18,941
Was that Marine
identified in the letter?

1094
01:06:19,013 --> 01:06:22,396
No. I notified the barracks C.O.
Colonel Jessup...

1095
01:06:22,470 --> 01:06:24,412
that I would be coming down
to investigate.

1096
01:06:24,486 --> 01:06:26,145
And what did you find?

1097
01:06:26,215 --> 01:06:29,149
The shift reported only one sentry
returned his weapon to the switch...

1098
01:06:29,222 --> 01:06:31,131
with a round of ammunition missing.

1099
01:06:31,206 --> 01:06:34,305
- Who was that?
- Lance Corporal Harold Dawson.

1100
01:06:34,374 --> 01:06:35,901
Your witness.

1101
01:06:38,471 --> 01:06:41,570
Mr. McGuire, have you questioned Dawson
about the fence line shooting?

1102
01:06:41,640 --> 01:06:45,437
Yes. He claims to have been engaged
in some manner by the enemy.

1103
01:06:45,512 --> 01:06:47,618
- You don' believe him?
- It's not my place--

1104
01:06:47,689 --> 01:06:49,827
Lance Corporal Dawson's been charged
with a number of crimes.

1105
01:06:49,896 --> 01:06:52,449
Why wasn’t he charged with firing
at the enemy without cause?

1106
01:06:54,152 --> 01:06:56,936
There wasn't enough evidence
to support such a charge.

1107
01:06:57,002 --> 01:06:58,856
Thank you.

1108
01:06:59,882 --> 01:07:01,922
Mr. McGuire, I don't understand
what you mean when you say...

1109
01:07:01,994 --> 01:07:04,482
'There wasn't enough evidence
to support such a charge.'

1110
01:07:04,554 --> 01:07:06,757
You had William Santiago's letter.

1111
01:07:07,977 --> 01:07:09,833
Santiago was the only eyewitness.

1112
01:07:09,898 --> 01:07:13,193
I never had the chance to interview him,
so I don't know what he saw.

1113
01:07:13,258 --> 01:07:16,193
And now we'll never know,
will we, Mr. McGuire?

1114
01:07:19,755 --> 01:07:22,569
- No more questions.
- The witness is excused.

1115
01:07:26,443 --> 01:07:29,029
Corporal Carl Edward Hammaker,
Marine Barracks...

1116
01:07:29,099 --> 01:07:32,231
Rifle Security Company Windward,
Second Platoon Bravo.

1117
01:07:32,300 --> 01:07:35,596
Corporal, were you present at a meeting
that Lieutenant Kendrick held...

1118
01:07:35,661 --> 01:07:38,890
on the afternoon of September 6
with the members of the Second Platoon?

1119
01:07:38,956 --> 01:07:40,201
Yes, sir.

1120
01:07:40,269 --> 01:07:42,756
Would you tell the court
the substance of that meeting?

1121
01:07:42,829 --> 01:07:45,862
Lieutenant Kendrick told us
we had an informer in our group--

1122
01:07:45,932 --> 01:07:48,518
that Private Santiago had gone
outside the chain of command...

1123
01:07:48,589 --> 01:07:51,404
and reported to the N.I.S.
on a member of our platoon.

1124
01:07:51,469 --> 01:07:55,213
Did that make you mad?
You can tell the truth, Corporal.

1125
01:07:55,278 --> 01:07:57,034
- Did it make you mad?
- Yes, sir.

1126
01:07:57,102 --> 01:07:58,280
How mad?

1127
01:07:58,351 --> 01:08:02,028
Private Santiago betrayed a code
we believe in very deeply, sir.

1128
01:08:02,094 --> 01:08:04,963
- Were the other squad members angry?
- Object. Speculation.

1129
01:08:05,038 --> 01:08:07,143
- Were Dawson and Downey?
- Is the government counsel...

1130
01:08:07,214 --> 01:08:11,591
honestly asking the witness to testify
as to how my clients felt?

1131
01:08:11,664 --> 01:08:13,518
Sustained.

1132
01:08:15,279 --> 01:08:19,076
Corporal, did Lieutenant Kendrick
leave a standing order at that meeting?

1133
01:08:19,152 --> 01:08:21,159
- Yes, sir.
- What was it?

1134
01:08:22,863 --> 01:08:26,726
Well, it was clear that he didn't want
us taking matters into our own hands.

1135
01:08:26,800 --> 01:08:28,709
What was the order?

1136
01:08:30,513 --> 01:08:33,361
Sir, he said Santiago
wasn't to be touched.

1137
01:08:34,865 --> 01:08:36,392
Your witness.

1138
01:08:37,425 --> 01:08:39,335
Corporal Hammaker, were you
in Dawson and Downey's barracks...

1139
01:08:39,410 --> 01:08:41,166
five minutes after this meeting?

1140
01:08:41,234 --> 01:08:42,728
No, sir.

1141
01:08:42,802 --> 01:08:45,354
Thanks.
I have no more questions.

1142
01:08:45,425 --> 01:08:47,401
The witness is excused.

1143
01:08:51,091 --> 01:08:53,294
The government calls
Corporal Raymond Thomas.

1144
01:08:53,363 --> 01:08:56,462
I understand Captain Ross is planning
on calling all the other members...

1145
01:08:56,531 --> 01:08:59,051
of Rifle Security Company Windward
to testify.

1146
01:08:59,123 --> 01:09:01,229
In light of the defense Lieutenant
Kaffee is planning to mount...

1147
01:09:01,300 --> 01:09:05,074
the explicit instructions of a platoon
leader seems particularly relevant.

1148
01:09:05,139 --> 01:09:07,562
The defense is willing to concede
that all 22 witnesses...

1149
01:09:07,636 --> 01:09:09,840
will testify substantially
as Corporal Hammaker did...

1150
01:09:09,908 --> 01:09:12,177
if the government is willing to concede
that none of them...

1151
01:09:12,244 --> 01:09:15,724
were in Dawson and Downey's room
at 16:20 on September 6.

1152
01:09:15,796 --> 01:09:17,652
Captain?

1153
01:09:17,717 --> 01:09:20,084
The government will stipulate.

1154
01:09:20,149 --> 01:09:23,946
Then we'll adjourn for the day.
You can call your next witness tomorrow.

1155
01:09:24,021 --> 01:09:25,877
All rise.

1156
01:09:36,885 --> 01:09:38,741
I want to go over the doctor again.

1157
01:09:38,806 --> 01:09:41,555
- We're taking the right approach.
- We've been over this already.

1158
01:09:41,623 --> 01:09:45,071
Listen to me. 3:00-- Stone says
he doesn't know what killed Santiago.

1159
01:09:45,143 --> 01:09:48,689
Then he meets with Jessup,
and at 5:00 he says it was poison?

1160
01:09:48,760 --> 01:09:51,378
- The doctor's not telling the truth.
- Oh, that's a relief!.

1161
01:09:51,447 --> 01:09:54,415
I was afraid I wouldn't be able to use
the 'liar, liar, pants on fire' defense.

1162
01:09:54,488 --> 01:09:59,124
We can't prove coercion.
Let's go over what we have, okay?

1163
01:10:09,049 --> 01:10:12,562
Private Santiago was admitted
to the E.R. at0012...

1164
01:10:12,633 --> 01:10:16,016
and he was pronounced dead
at 0037.

1165
01:10:16,090 --> 01:10:19,156
Dr. Stone, what is lactic acidosis?

1166
01:10:19,226 --> 01:10:22,226
If the muscles and other cells
of the body burn sugar...

1167
01:10:22,298 --> 01:10:25,049
instead of oxygen,
lactic acid is produced.

1168
01:10:25,115 --> 01:10:28,410
That lactic acid is what caused
Santiago's lungs to bleed.

1169
01:10:28,475 --> 01:10:31,290
Normally, how long does it take
for the muscles and other cells...

1170
01:10:31,356 --> 01:10:33,690
to begin burning sugar
instead of oxygen?

1171
01:10:33,755 --> 01:10:36,210
Twenty to thirty minutes.

1172
01:10:36,283 --> 01:10:39,862
And what caused this process
to be sped up in Santiago's muscles?

1173
01:10:39,932 --> 01:10:42,005
An ingested poison of some kind.

1174
01:10:42,076 --> 01:10:45,010
Your Honor, we object at this point.
The witness is speculating.

1175
01:10:45,084 --> 01:10:47,059
Commander Stone is an expert
medical witness.

1176
01:10:47,132 --> 01:10:49,499
In this courtroom, his opinion
is not considered speculation.

1177
01:10:49,564 --> 01:10:52,433
Commander Stone is an internist,
not a criminologist.

1178
01:10:52,508 --> 01:10:54,964
The medical facts here
are ultimately inconclusive.

1179
01:10:55,037 --> 01:10:58,583
A point I'm confident you’ll illustrate
to the court under cross-examination.

1180
01:10:58,653 --> 01:11:01,687
So I'm sure you won't mind
if his opinion is admitted now.

1181
01:11:01,758 --> 01:11:03,449
Not at all, sir.

1182
01:11:05,854 --> 01:11:09,848
Dr. Stone, did Willie Santiago
die of poisoning?

1183
01:11:09,918 --> 01:11:11,543
Absolutely.

1184
01:11:11,614 --> 01:11:15,543
You're aware that the lab and coroner's
report show no traces of poison?

1185
01:11:15,615 --> 01:11:18,037
- Yes, I am.
- Then how do you justify--

1186
01:11:18,111 --> 01:11:20,958
There are literally dozens of toxins
which are virtually undetectable...

1187
01:11:21,023 --> 01:11:23,577
both in the human body
and on a fabric.

1188
01:11:23,648 --> 01:11:27,161
The nature of the acidosis
is the compelling factor on this issue.

1189
01:11:28,000 --> 01:11:29,822
Thank you, sir.

1190
01:11:31,680 --> 01:11:34,876
Commander, is it possible for a person
to have an affliction--

1191
01:11:34,943 --> 01:11:39,135
some sort of condition-- which might
speed up the process of acidosis?

1192
01:11:41,761 --> 01:11:43,549
Commander, is it possible?

1193
01:11:43,616 --> 01:11:45,406
It's possible.

1194
01:11:45,474 --> 01:11:47,775
What might some of those
conditions be?

1195
01:11:48,801 --> 01:11:51,190
If a person had a coronary disorder...

1196
01:11:51,265 --> 01:11:54,200
or a cerebral disorder,
the process would be more rapid.

1197
01:11:54,274 --> 01:11:58,137
If had a coronary condition and
a clean rag was placed in my mouth...

1198
01:11:58,210 --> 01:12:01,823
and the rag was pushed too far down,
is it possible that my cells...

1199
01:12:01,891 --> 01:12:04,541
would continue burning sugar
after the rag was taken out?

1200
01:12:04,610 --> 01:12:07,392
It would have to be
a very serious condition.

1201
01:12:07,459 --> 01:12:09,630
Is it possible to have
a serious coronary condition...

1202
01:12:09,699 --> 01:12:12,993
where the warning signals were so mild
as to escape a physician...

1203
01:12:13,060 --> 01:12:15,482
during a routine medical exam?

1204
01:12:15,556 --> 01:12:18,687
Possibly. There would still
be symptoms, though.

1205
01:12:18,756 --> 01:12:20,992
- What kind of symptoms?
- There are hundreds--

1206
01:12:21,059 --> 01:12:23,264
- Chest pains?
- Yes.

1207
01:12:23,333 --> 01:12:25,187
- Shortness of breath?
- Yes.

1208
01:12:25,253 --> 01:12:27,587
- Fatigue?
- Of course.

1209
01:12:32,966 --> 01:12:34,820
Doctor, is this your signature?

1210
01:12:36,389 --> 01:12:37,470
Yes, it is.

1211
01:12:38,182 --> 01:12:41,695
This is an order for Private Santiago
to be put on restrictive duty.

1212
01:12:41,766 --> 01:12:45,541
Would you read your handwritten remarks
at the bottom of the page, please?

1213
01:12:45,606 --> 01:12:49,632
'Initial testing, negative.
Patient complains of chest pains...

1214
01:12:49,702 --> 01:12:51,775
shortness of breath and fatigue.

1215
01:12:51,846 --> 01:12:55,425
Restricted from running distances
over five miles for one week.'

1216
01:12:58,150 --> 01:13:01,534
Commander, isn't it possible
that Santiago had a serious condition...

1217
01:13:01,607 --> 01:13:06,342
and it was that condition that caused
the accelerated chemical reaction?

1218
01:13:07,944 --> 01:13:09,505
It's not possible?

1219
01:13:10,921 --> 01:13:14,335
I personally give each man
a thorough physical examination.

1220
01:13:14,408 --> 01:13:17,376
Private Santiago was given
a clean bill of health.

1221
01:13:17,449 --> 01:13:19,904
That's why it had to be poison,
right, Commander?

1222
01:13:19,977 --> 01:13:23,906
'Cause if you put a man with a serious
coronary condition on duty...

1223
01:13:23,977 --> 01:13:26,311
and that man died
from a heart-related incident...

1224
01:13:26,377 --> 01:13:28,287
you'd have a lot to answer for,
wouldn’t you, Doctor?

1225
01:13:28,362 --> 01:13:31,265
- Object! Move to strike.
- Sustained.

1226
01:13:32,490 --> 01:13:34,400
I have no more questions,
Your Honor.

1227
01:13:35,690 --> 01:13:38,953
Dr. Stone, you've held
a medical license for 17 years.

1228
01:13:39,019 --> 01:13:41,091
You're Board-certified
in internal medicine.

1229
01:13:41,162 --> 01:13:46,499
You are chief of internal medicine
at a hospital which serves 5,426 people.

1230
01:13:46,572 --> 01:13:51,241
In your professional medical opinion,
was Willie Santiago poisoned?

1231
01:13:51,307 --> 01:13:53,926
We renew our objection
to Commander Stone's testimony...

1232
01:13:53,996 --> 01:13:56,035
and ask that it be stricken
from the record.

1233
01:13:56,107 --> 01:13:59,883
We further ask the court members to lend
no weight to this witness's testimony.

1234
01:13:59,948 --> 01:14:01,541
The objection is overruled.

1235
01:14:01,613 --> 01:14:05,541
The defense strenuously objects
and requests an 802 conference...

1236
01:14:05,612 --> 01:14:09,574
so that His Honor might have a chance
to hear discussion before ruling.

1237
01:14:09,646 --> 01:14:12,994
The objection of the defense
has been heard and overruled.

1238
01:14:13,069 --> 01:14:15,655
- Move to reconsider.
- Your objection is noted.

1239
01:14:15,725 --> 01:14:19,467
The witness is an expert,
and the court will hear his opinion!

1240
01:14:23,598 --> 01:14:28,235
Dr. Stone, in your expert,
professional opinion...

1241
01:14:28,302 --> 01:14:30,921
was Willie Santiago poisoned?

1242
01:14:30,991 --> 01:14:32,878
Yes.

1243
01:14:32,943 --> 01:14:36,522
Thank you, sir.
I have no more questions.

1244
01:14:36,591 --> 01:14:38,598
Commander, you may step down.

1245
01:14:42,960 --> 01:14:47,019
Please the court, while we reserve
the right to call rebuttal witnesses...

1246
01:14:47,089 --> 01:14:48,779
the government rests.

1247
01:14:48,848 --> 01:14:52,297
We'll stand in recess until 1000,
Monday the 19th...

1248
01:14:52,369 --> 01:14:55,664
at which time, the defense
will call its first witness.

1249
01:14:55,729 --> 01:14:57,584
All rise.

1250
01:15:06,322 --> 01:15:08,362
'I strenuously object'?

1251
01:15:08,434 --> 01:15:12,492
Is that how it works?
'Objection overruled.'

1252
01:15:12,561 --> 01:15:14,635
' No, no. I strenuously object.'

1253
01:15:14,707 --> 01:15:18,023
'Oh, well, if you strenuously object,
then I should take time to reconsider.'

1254
01:15:18,098 --> 01:15:19,626
I got it on the record.

1255
01:15:19,699 --> 01:15:21,805
You also got the court members
thinking we're afraid of the doctor.

1256
01:15:21,876 --> 01:15:24,461
You object once, so they can hear us say
he's not a criminologist.

1257
01:15:24,532 --> 01:15:28,012
You keep after it, and suddenly it looks
like a bunch of fancy lawyer tricks.

1258
01:15:28,083 --> 01:15:31,051
It's the difference between paper law
and trial law.

1259
01:15:31,124 --> 01:15:33,490
You even had the judge saying
Stone was an expert!

1260
01:15:33,556 --> 01:15:36,306
She made a mistake.
Let's not relive it.

1261
01:15:37,974 --> 01:15:41,388
I'm gonna go call my wife.
I'll see you tonight.

1262
01:15:43,444 --> 01:15:45,747
Why do you hate them so much?

1263
01:15:45,813 --> 01:15:48,180
They beat up on a weakling.
That's all they did.

1264
01:15:48,245 --> 01:15:51,148
The rest of this is just
smoke-filled coffeehouse crap.

1265
01:15:51,221 --> 01:15:54,221
They tortured and tormented
a weaker kid!

1266
01:15:54,294 --> 01:15:56,236
They didn't like him,
so they killed him.

1267
01:15:56,310 --> 01:15:59,093
And why? Because
he couldn't run very fast!

1268
01:15:59,159 --> 01:16:02,671
All right.
Everybody take the night off.

1269
01:16:02,742 --> 01:16:04,597
- I'm sorry.
- I know.

1270
01:16:04,662 --> 01:16:07,313
We've been working 20 hours a day
for three and half weeks straight.

1271
01:16:07,383 --> 01:16:10,612
Just take the night off.
Go see your wife, your daughter.

1272
01:16:10,678 --> 01:16:12,751
Jo, go do...

1273
01:16:14,040 --> 01:16:17,423
whatever it is you do
when you're not here.

1274
01:16:17,496 --> 01:16:20,081
- What day is tomorrow?
- Saturday.

1275
01:16:20,152 --> 01:16:22,007
We start at 10:00.

1276
01:16:25,848 --> 01:16:28,084
Why do you like them so much?

1277
01:16:32,152 --> 01:16:34,258
'Cause they stand on a wall....

1278
01:16:34,329 --> 01:16:38,388
and they say, ' Nothing's gonna hurt you
tonight, not on my watch.'

1279
01:16:42,809 --> 01:16:46,006
Don't worry about the doctor.
This trial starts Monday.

1280
01:16:50,810 --> 01:16:54,837
1 and 2 with two out.
And a line drive to left center.

1281
01:16:54,907 --> 01:16:58,005
Kirby racing.
He won’t get there.

1282
01:16:58,075 --> 01:17:01,075
And rounding third is Cal Ripken...

1283
01:17:01,148 --> 01:17:04,181
and the Twins' streak is over.

1284
01:17:07,260 --> 01:17:10,872
One strike away, and Andy Milligan
feels right now like Hulk Hogan.

1285
01:17:13,885 --> 01:17:16,884
I'm sorry to bother you.
I should've called first.

1286
01:17:16,957 --> 01:17:21,148
No, I was just watching
a ball game. Come on in.

1287
01:17:35,455 --> 01:17:40,692
I was wondering if-- How you’d feel
about my taking you to dinner tonight?

1288
01:17:40,766 --> 01:17:43,636
- Are you asking me out on a date?
- No.

1289
01:17:43,711 --> 01:17:45,653
Sounded like you
were asking me on a date.

1290
01:17:45,727 --> 01:17:48,629
I've been asked out on dates before,
and that's what it sounded like.

1291
01:17:49,856 --> 01:17:51,929
Do you like seafood?
I know a good seafood place.

1292
01:18:00,417 --> 01:18:02,391
My third case was
a drunk and disorderly.

1293
01:18:02,464 --> 01:18:06,174
It lasted nine weeks. I rounded up
31 people from the bar that night.

1294
01:18:06,240 --> 01:18:09,536
Nine weeks on a D and D?
What was the prosecutor offering?

1295
01:18:09,601 --> 01:18:11,456
Fifteen days.

1296
01:18:14,146 --> 01:18:15,739
You sure hustled
the shit out of him.

1297
01:18:15,810 --> 01:18:18,079
Well, after that
they moved me to Internal Affairs.

1298
01:18:18,146 --> 01:18:20,056
- Tough to blame them.
- Where I have earned...

1299
01:18:20,130 --> 01:18:23,675
two meritorious service medals
and two letters of commendation.

1300
01:18:23,746 --> 01:18:26,649
Why are you always giving me
your resume?

1301
01:18:30,371 --> 01:18:32,226
Because I want you to think
I'm a good lawyer.

1302
01:18:32,291 --> 01:18:34,233
I do.

1303
01:18:34,307 --> 01:18:36,413
No, you don't.

1304
01:18:39,715 --> 01:18:41,886
I think you’re an exceptional lawyer.

1305
01:18:42,660 --> 01:18:47,101
I watch the court members.
They respond to you. They like you.

1306
01:18:47,172 --> 01:18:49,692
I see you convincing them,
and I think Dawson and Downey...

1307
01:18:49,764 --> 01:18:52,318
are gonna end up
owing their lives to you.

1308
01:18:55,812 --> 01:18:57,668
Jo, I think--

1309
01:18:59,301 --> 01:19:02,813
I think you should prepare yourself
for the fact that we're gonna lose.

1310
01:19:02,885 --> 01:19:06,115
Ross's opening statement--
it was all true.

1311
01:19:06,182 --> 01:19:08,833
Let's pretend for a minute
that it would actually matter...

1312
01:19:08,902 --> 01:19:10,909
that the guys
were given an order.

1313
01:19:10,982 --> 01:19:13,503
I can't prove it ever happened.

1314
01:19:13,575 --> 01:19:15,964
We'll keep doing what we're doing
and we'll put on a show...

1315
01:19:16,038 --> 01:19:21,221
but all we have is the testimony
of two people accused of murder.

1316
01:19:22,376 --> 01:19:24,164
We'll find Markinson.

1317
01:19:24,232 --> 01:19:28,542
Jo, we're gonna lose,
and we're gonna lose huge.

1318
01:19:31,624 --> 01:19:34,789
Corporal Jeffrey Owen Barnes,
Marine Barracks Windward...

1319
01:19:34,857 --> 01:19:36,799
Guantanamo Bay, Cuba.

1320
01:19:36,872 --> 01:19:41,030
Corporal Barnes, name some reasons
why a Marine would receive a Code Red.

1321
01:19:41,097 --> 01:19:44,359
Being late for platoon
or company meetings.

1322
01:19:44,425 --> 01:19:48,167
Keeping his barracks in disorder.
Falling back on a run.

1323
01:19:48,233 --> 01:19:50,623
- Have you ever received a Code Red?
- Yes, sir.

1324
01:19:50,698 --> 01:19:54,112
We were doing seven-man assault drills,
and my weapon slipped.

1325
01:19:54,185 --> 01:19:57,350
It was 'cause it was over 100 degrees,
and my palms were sweaty...

1326
01:19:57,418 --> 01:20:00,932
and I'd forgotten to use the resin
like we were taught.

1327
01:20:01,002 --> 01:20:02,464
What happened?

1328
01:20:02,539 --> 01:20:05,474
That night, the guys in my squad
threw a blanket over me...

1329
01:20:05,547 --> 01:20:08,264
took turns punching me in the arm
for five minutes...

1330
01:20:08,331 --> 01:20:10,818
then they poured glue on my hands.

1331
01:20:10,891 --> 01:20:14,437
And it worked too, 'cause
I ain't never dropped my weapon since.

1332
01:20:15,851 --> 01:20:18,786
Was Private Santiago ever late
for platoon meetings?

1333
01:20:18,860 --> 01:20:19,973
Yes, sir.

1334
01:20:20,044 --> 01:20:22,313
- Was his barracks ever in disorder?
- Yes, sir.

1335
01:20:22,380 --> 01:20:24,617
- Did he ever fall back on a run?
- All the time, sir.

1336
01:20:24,685 --> 01:20:29,835
Did he ever, prior to the night
of September 6, receive a Code Red?

1337
01:20:29,900 --> 01:20:31,329
No, sir.

1338
01:20:31,405 --> 01:20:33,379
- Never?
- No, sir.

1339
01:20:34,990 --> 01:20:37,259
You got a Code Red
'cause your palms were sweaty.

1340
01:20:37,326 --> 01:20:41,220
Why didn't Santiago,
this burden to his unit, ever get one?

1341
01:20:42,638 --> 01:20:44,580
Dawson wouldn't allow it, sir.

1342
01:20:45,646 --> 01:20:47,621
Dawson wouldn't allow it.

1343
01:20:47,694 --> 01:20:51,142
The guys talked tough about Santiago,
but they wouldn’t go near him.

1344
01:20:51,215 --> 01:20:53,070
They were too afraid of Dawson.

1345
01:20:53,135 --> 01:20:55,502
Object.
The witness is speculating.

1346
01:20:55,567 --> 01:20:59,080
I'll rephrase. Jeffrey, did you ever
want to give Santiago a Code Red?

1347
01:20:59,151 --> 01:21:01,038
- Yes, sir.
- Why didn’t you?

1348
01:21:01,104 --> 01:21:03,787
'Cause Dawson
would kick my butt, sir.

1349
01:21:03,855 --> 01:21:07,630
Good enough. Captain Ross
is gonna ask you some questions now.

1350
01:21:08,944 --> 01:21:10,799
Corporal Barnes...

1351
01:21:12,208 --> 01:21:14,598
I hold here the Marine Outline
for Recruit Training.

1352
01:21:14,673 --> 01:21:16,363
- Are you familiar with this book?
- Yes, sir.

1353
01:21:16,432 --> 01:21:18,025
- Have you read it?
- Yes, sir.

1354
01:21:18,097 --> 01:21:21,262
Would you turn to the chapter
that deals with Code Reds, please?

1355
01:21:23,729 --> 01:21:27,145
Just flip to the page of the book
that discusses Code Reds.

1356
01:21:29,329 --> 01:21:32,646
Well, you see, sir, Code Red
is a term that we use.

1357
01:21:32,722 --> 01:21:34,348
Just down in Gitmo--

1358
01:21:34,419 --> 01:21:36,426
Oh, we're in luck, then.

1359
01:21:39,602 --> 01:21:43,858
Standard Operating Procedure, Rifle
Security Company, Guantanamo Bay, Cuba.

1360
01:21:43,923 --> 01:21:47,752
I assume we'll find the term Code Red
and its definition in that book.

1361
01:21:47,826 --> 01:21:49,616
No, sir.

1362
01:21:49,683 --> 01:21:51,407
Corporal Barnes, I'm a Marine.

1363
01:21:51,476 --> 01:21:55,437
Is there no book, no manual or pamphlet,
no set of orders or regulations...

1364
01:21:55,508 --> 01:21:59,851
that lets me know that as a Marine one
of my duties is to perform Code Reds?

1365
01:21:59,925 --> 01:22:03,219
No, sir.
No book, sir.

1366
01:22:03,284 --> 01:22:05,139
No further questions.

1367
01:22:07,124 --> 01:22:09,580
Corporal, would you turn
to the page in this book....

1368
01:22:09,653 --> 01:22:11,956
that says where
the mess hall is, please?

1369
01:22:12,022 --> 01:22:14,989
Lieutenant Kaffee,
that's not in the book, sir.

1370
01:22:16,469 --> 01:22:19,285
You mean to say in all your time
at Gitmo you've never had a meal?

1371
01:22:19,350 --> 01:22:22,383
No, sir.
Three squares a day, sir.

1372
01:22:23,158 --> 01:22:24,685
I don't understand.

1373
01:22:24,757 --> 01:22:27,693
How did you know where the mess hall was
if it’s not in this book?

1374
01:22:30,200 --> 01:22:33,233
Well, I guess I just followed the crowd
at chow time, sir.

1375
01:22:34,168 --> 01:22:36,273
No more questions.

1376
01:22:36,343 --> 01:22:39,856
- Corporal Barnes, you may step down.
- Thank you, sir.

1377
01:22:45,240 --> 01:22:47,629
7:00 tonight we'll do
a final Kendrick review.

1378
01:22:47,704 --> 01:22:50,487
I want to slam-dunk this guy.

1379
01:23:01,465 --> 01:23:02,959
Hey, Luther.

1380
01:23:03,033 --> 01:23:05,424
Admiral, how's
the big case going?

1381
01:23:05,498 --> 01:23:07,386
Nose to the grindstone.

1382
01:23:07,450 --> 01:23:10,483
- No flies on you.
- A rolling stone gathers no moss.

1383
01:23:10,554 --> 01:23:12,976
Well, it ain't over
till the fat lady sings.

1384
01:23:13,051 --> 01:23:15,320
You can say that again.

1385
01:23:15,386 --> 01:23:18,551
- It ain't over till the fat lady sings.
- Till the fat lady sings.

1386
01:23:19,611 --> 01:23:21,466
Walked into that one.

1387
01:23:32,540 --> 01:23:35,159
Oh, Jesus Christ!

1388
01:23:35,229 --> 01:23:37,781
You left the door unlocked.

1389
01:23:37,852 --> 01:23:40,788
- You scared the shit out of me.
-Just keep driving.

1390
01:23:40,861 --> 01:23:42,716
Are you aware
you're under subpoena?

1391
01:23:42,781 --> 01:23:46,425
Yes. I'm also aware that the lives
of two Marines are in your hands.

1392
01:23:46,493 --> 01:23:48,567
If there was something
I could do about that, I would.

1393
01:23:48,638 --> 01:23:50,939
But since I can't,
all I can do is help you.

1394
01:23:51,005 --> 01:23:53,242
- What do you know?
- I know everything.

1395
01:23:53,310 --> 01:23:55,449
- Was it a Code Red?
- Yes.

1396
01:23:55,518 --> 01:23:57,558
- Did Kendrick give the order?
- Yes.

1397
01:23:57,630 --> 01:24:00,444
- Did you witness it?
- I didn't need to.

1398
01:24:00,509 --> 01:24:03,031
Then how do you know?
You know shit.

1399
01:24:03,103 --> 01:24:05,372
He was never gonna be transferred
off that base.

1400
01:24:11,071 --> 01:24:14,235
Jessup was gonna keep him on the base.
He said he wanted him trained.

1401
01:24:14,303 --> 01:24:16,790
- The transfer order has your signature.
- Yeah, I know.

1402
01:24:16,863 --> 01:24:20,662
I signed it the morning you arrived
in Cuba, five days after Santiago died.

1403
01:24:24,193 --> 01:24:26,844
I'm gonna get you a deal, some kind
of immunity with the prosecutor.

1404
01:24:26,913 --> 01:24:31,223
In about four days, you'll appear
as a witness and tell what you know.

1405
01:24:31,296 --> 01:24:34,777
I'm gonna check you into a motel.
We are gonna start from the beginning.

1406
01:24:34,849 --> 01:24:38,843
I don't want a deal,
and I don't want immunity.

1407
01:24:38,913 --> 01:24:43,933
I want you to know that I'm proud
neither of what I've done or am doing.

1408
01:24:46,178 --> 01:24:48,067
- Where is he?
- The Downtown Lodge in Northeast.

1409
01:24:48,131 --> 01:24:50,170
- I want him guarded.
- That's a good idea.

1410
01:24:50,242 --> 01:24:52,828
- My clearance code is 411527273.
- Clearance code?

1411
01:24:52,899 --> 01:24:55,452
- Thank you.
- Do you have a clearance code?

1412
01:24:55,523 --> 01:24:57,564
This is Jo Galloway.
I need to secure a witness.

1413
01:24:57,636 --> 01:25:00,483
Anyway, he also said that Jessup’s lying
about the transportation off the base.

1414
01:25:00,547 --> 01:25:03,231
Jessup said that 6:00 the next morning
was the first flight leaving.

1415
01:25:03,300 --> 01:25:06,649
Markinson says there was a plane
that left seven hours earlier.

1416
01:25:06,724 --> 01:25:09,626
That was impressive. Did you hear
what I said about the flight?

1417
01:25:09,699 --> 01:25:12,831
Sam, when a flight takes off,
there's a record kept, right?

1418
01:25:12,900 --> 01:25:15,005
Yeah, you need the tower chief’s log
from Gitmo.

1419
01:25:15,076 --> 01:25:18,078
- Get it.
- We're gonna win.

1420
01:25:18,150 --> 01:25:20,419
We don't know who Markinson is.
We don't know what the logbook will say.

1421
01:25:20,486 --> 01:25:23,387
You just concentrate on Downey.
I'm gonna tell Ross where we are.

1422
01:25:30,213 --> 01:25:33,509
Nice work today.
Redirect on Barnes.

1423
01:25:33,574 --> 01:25:37,536
- I have Markinson.
- Where is he?

1424
01:25:37,607 --> 01:25:41,764
Motel room in Northeast with
six Federal Marshalls outside his door.

1425
01:25:41,831 --> 01:25:43,903
The transfer that Markinson
signed is phony.

1426
01:25:43,975 --> 01:25:46,692
Jessup's statement that the 6:00 a.m.
flight was the first available is a lie.

1427
01:25:46,759 --> 01:25:49,094
We're checking the tower chief’s log.
I'd like a beer, please.

1428
01:25:49,159 --> 01:25:53,415
In the meantime, I'm gonna put Kendrick
on the stand and have some fun.

1429
01:25:53,480 --> 01:25:56,132
All right, I have
an obligation to tell you...

1430
01:25:56,201 --> 01:25:59,168
that if you accuse Kendrick or Jessup
of any crime without proper evidence...

1431
01:25:59,241 --> 01:26:01,891
you'll be subject to a court-martial
for professional misconduct.

1432
01:26:01,960 --> 01:26:06,271
That's something that'll be stapled to
every job application you ever fill out.

1433
01:26:07,881 --> 01:26:11,297
Markinson's not gonna hold up, Danny.
He's a crazy man.

1434
01:26:11,370 --> 01:26:14,850
I'm not saying this to intimidate you.
I'm being your lawyer here.

1435
01:26:14,921 --> 01:26:18,850
Thanks, Jack. And I think the fucking
bunch of you are certifiably insane.

1436
01:26:18,922 --> 01:26:21,158
Your code of honor makes me
want to beat the shit out of somebody.

1437
01:26:21,226 --> 01:26:24,937
Don't lump me in with them
just because we wear the same uniform.

1438
01:26:25,003 --> 01:26:27,937
I'm your friend, and I don't think
your clients belong in jail...

1439
01:26:28,010 --> 01:26:29,865
but I don't get
to make that decision.

1440
01:26:29,930 --> 01:26:34,154
I represent the United States government
without passion or prejudice.

1441
01:26:34,219 --> 01:26:37,415
- My client has a case.
- Here you go.

1442
01:26:41,100 --> 01:26:43,783
I want you to acknowledge that
the judge advocate has made you aware...

1443
01:26:43,852 --> 01:26:46,601
of the possible consequences involved
in accusing a Marine officer...

1444
01:26:46,667 --> 01:26:48,676
of a felony
without proper evidence.

1445
01:26:48,749 --> 01:26:51,302
I've been so advised.

1446
01:26:55,341 --> 01:26:58,024
You got bullied
into that courtroom, Danny.

1447
01:26:58,093 --> 01:27:01,803
By everyone.
By Dawson, by Galloway.

1448
01:27:01,870 --> 01:27:04,324
Shit, I practically dared you.

1449
01:27:05,453 --> 01:27:08,836
You got bullied into that courtroom
by the memory of a dead lawyer.

1450
01:27:14,702 --> 01:27:17,703
You're a lousy fucking
softball player, Jack!

1451
01:27:20,943 --> 01:27:24,937
Your boys are going down, Danny.
I can't stop it anymore.

1452
01:27:30,032 --> 01:27:33,229
Lieutenant Kendrick, in your opinion,
was Private Santiago a good Marine?

1453
01:27:33,296 --> 01:27:35,303
I'd say he was about average.

1454
01:27:35,376 --> 01:27:38,638
You signed three proficiency
and conduct reports on Santiago.

1455
01:27:38,704 --> 01:27:42,217
On all three reports, you indicate
a rating of below average.

1456
01:27:45,458 --> 01:27:49,233
Yes, Private Santiago
was below average.

1457
01:27:49,298 --> 01:27:52,910
I did not see the need
to trample on a man's grave.

1458
01:27:52,978 --> 01:27:55,051
We appreciate that,
but you’re under oath now.

1459
01:27:55,122 --> 01:27:57,642
Unpleasant as it may be,
we'd all just as soon hear the truth.

1460
01:27:57,714 --> 01:27:59,502
I'm aware of my oath.

1461
01:27:59,569 --> 01:28:04,328
These are the last three pro-con reports
you signed for Lance Corporal Dawson.

1462
01:28:04,404 --> 01:28:06,258
Dawson received
two marks of exceptional...

1463
01:28:06,323 --> 01:28:10,514
but on this most recent report of June 9
he received a rating of below average.

1464
01:28:10,579 --> 01:28:14,408
- I'd like to discuss this last report.
- That would be fine.

1465
01:28:14,483 --> 01:28:17,997
Lance Corporal Dawson's ranking after
the school of infantry was perfect.

1466
01:28:18,068 --> 01:28:20,882
Over half that class has since
been promoted to full corporal...

1467
01:28:20,947 --> 01:28:23,152
while Dawson has remained
a lance corporal.

1468
01:28:23,220 --> 01:28:26,090
Was Dawson's promotion held up
because of this last report?

1469
01:28:26,165 --> 01:28:28,020
I'm sure it was.

1470
01:28:28,085 --> 01:28:30,954
Do you recall why Dawson was given
such a poor grade on this report?

1471
01:28:31,029 --> 01:28:32,273
I'm sure I don't.

1472
01:28:32,342 --> 01:28:36,018
I have many men in my charge.
I write many reports.

1473
01:28:36,085 --> 01:28:41,618
Lieutenant, do you recall an incident
involving a P.F.C. Curtis Bell...

1474
01:28:41,687 --> 01:28:44,304
who'd been found stealing liquor
from the Officers' Club?

1475
01:28:44,374 --> 01:28:46,197
Yes, I do.

1476
01:28:46,263 --> 01:28:48,597
Did you report Private Bell
to proper authorities?

1477
01:28:50,423 --> 01:28:52,495
I have two books at my bedside--

1478
01:28:52,567 --> 01:28:55,437
The Marine Corps Code of Conduct
and The King James Bible.

1479
01:28:55,511 --> 01:28:57,998
The only proper authorities I'm aware of
are my commanding officer...

1480
01:28:58,071 --> 01:29:00,625
Colonel Nathan R. Jessup
and the Lord our God.

1481
01:29:02,169 --> 01:29:04,624
At your request, Lieutenant Kendrick,
I can have the record reflect...

1482
01:29:04,696 --> 01:29:07,249
your lack of acknowledgement
of this court as a proper authority.

1483
01:29:07,320 --> 01:29:10,038
- Objection. Argumentative.
- Sustained.

1484
01:29:10,104 --> 01:29:12,111
Watch yourself, counselor.

1485
01:29:12,184 --> 01:29:14,769
Did you report Private Bell
to your superiors?

1486
01:29:14,840 --> 01:29:17,492
I remember thinking very highly
of Private Bell--

1487
01:29:17,561 --> 01:29:20,595
not wanting to see his record tarnished
by a formal charge.

1488
01:29:21,722 --> 01:29:24,472
You preferred it be handled
within the unit?

1489
01:29:26,138 --> 01:29:27,992
Yes, I most certainly did.

1490
01:29:29,177 --> 01:29:32,277
- Do you know what a Code Red is?
- Yes, I do.

1491
01:29:32,346 --> 01:29:35,412
- Have you ever ordered a Code Red?
- No, I have not.

1492
01:29:35,482 --> 01:29:38,451
Did you order Dawson and two other men
to make sure that Private Bell...

1493
01:29:38,523 --> 01:29:43,738
received no food or drink, except water,
for a period of seven days?

1494
01:29:43,803 --> 01:29:46,008
That is a distortion
of the truth, Lieutenant.

1495
01:29:46,076 --> 01:29:48,247
Private Bell was placed
on barracks restriction.

1496
01:29:48,315 --> 01:29:51,282
He was given water and vitamin
supplements, and I can assure you...

1497
01:29:51,355 --> 01:29:55,153
at no time
was his health in danger.

1498
01:29:55,228 --> 01:29:57,846
I'm sure it was lovely
for Private Bell.

1499
01:29:57,916 --> 01:30:00,470
But you did order
the barracks restriction, didn’t you?

1500
01:30:00,541 --> 01:30:04,534
- You did order the denial of food?
- Yes, I did.

1501
01:30:04,605 --> 01:30:08,250
Wouldn't this form of discipline
be considered a Code Red?

1502
01:30:10,942 --> 01:30:14,652
If called the other 478 Marines
at Guantanamo Bay to testify...

1503
01:30:14,718 --> 01:30:16,726
would they consider it
a Code Red?

1504
01:30:16,799 --> 01:30:20,595
The witness can't possibly testify
as to what 478 other men would say.

1505
01:30:20,670 --> 01:30:24,380
We object to this entire line
of questioning. It's argumentative...

1506
01:30:24,446 --> 01:30:26,715
and irrelevant badgering
of the witness.

1507
01:30:26,782 --> 01:30:29,303
The government's objection
is sustained, Lieutenant Kaffee...

1508
01:30:29,374 --> 01:30:32,376
and I would remind you that you’re now
questioning a Marine officer...

1509
01:30:32,448 --> 01:30:34,488
with an impeccable service record.

1510
01:30:34,560 --> 01:30:36,054
Thank you, Your Honor.

1511
01:30:37,087 --> 01:30:40,732
Lieutenant, was Dawson given a rating
of below average on this last report...

1512
01:30:40,800 --> 01:30:43,550
because you learned he'd been sneaking
food to Private Bell?

1513
01:30:43,616 --> 01:30:46,748
- Object!
- Not so fast. Lieutenant?

1514
01:30:48,352 --> 01:30:51,866
Lance Corporal Dawson
was given a below average rating...

1515
01:30:52,802 --> 01:30:55,168
because he had committed a crime.

1516
01:30:55,233 --> 01:30:58,364
A crime?
What crime did he commit?

1517
01:31:02,114 --> 01:31:07,646
Dawson brought a hungry guy some food.
What crime did he commit?

1518
01:31:09,571 --> 01:31:11,065
He disobeyed an order.

1519
01:31:11,139 --> 01:31:13,527
And because he exercised
his own set of values...

1520
01:31:13,602 --> 01:31:16,472
because he made a decision
about the welfare of a Marine...

1521
01:31:16,547 --> 01:31:20,027
that was in conflict with your order,
he was punished, is that right?

1522
01:31:20,099 --> 01:31:23,482
Lance Corporal Dawson
disobeyed an order.

1523
01:31:23,555 --> 01:31:25,976
Yeah, but it wasn't
a real order, was it?

1524
01:31:26,051 --> 01:31:28,157
After all, it's peacetime.

1525
01:31:28,228 --> 01:31:31,360
He wasn't being asked to secure a hill
or advance on a beachhead.

1526
01:31:31,429 --> 01:31:35,684
I mean, surely a Marine
of Dawson's intelligence...

1527
01:31:35,748 --> 01:31:38,716
can be trusted to determine on his own
which are the important orders...

1528
01:31:38,789 --> 01:31:42,531
and which orders might, say,
be morally questionable?

1529
01:31:45,637 --> 01:31:47,361
Can he?

1530
01:31:47,430 --> 01:31:50,943
Can Dawson determine on his own
which orders he's going to follow?

1531
01:31:51,014 --> 01:31:52,640
No, he cannot.

1532
01:31:52,711 --> 01:31:55,329
A lesson he learned
after the Curtis Bell incident, right?

1533
01:31:55,398 --> 01:31:58,147
- I would think so.
- You know so, don’t you?

1534
01:31:58,214 --> 01:31:59,841
- Object!
- Sustained.

1535
01:32:01,799 --> 01:32:04,613
Lieutenant Kendrick,
one final question.

1536
01:32:05,863 --> 01:32:09,027
If you had ordered Dawson
to give Santiago a Code Red--

1537
01:32:09,096 --> 01:32:13,154
- I specifically ordered those men--
- Would he disobey you again?

1538
01:32:13,224 --> 01:32:17,119
- Lieutenant, don't answer that!
- You don't have to. I'm through.

1539
01:32:17,192 --> 01:32:20,672
Lieutenant Kendrick, did you order
Lance Corporal Dawson...

1540
01:32:20,744 --> 01:32:24,542
and Private Downey
to give Willie Santiago a Code Red?

1541
01:32:27,625 --> 01:32:30,473
- No, I did not.
- Thank you.

1542
01:32:34,281 --> 01:32:36,354
What's the word?

1543
01:32:36,425 --> 01:32:40,516
I got the tower chief’s log from that
night. Jessup’s telling the truth.

1544
01:32:40,585 --> 01:32:44,646
- 6:00 a.m. flight was the first plane.
- Let me see this.

1545
01:32:54,411 --> 01:32:57,160
- Working late tonight?
- Oh, yeah.

1546
01:33:01,356 --> 01:33:04,902
There wasn't a flight at00.
What the fuck are you trying to pull?

1547
01:33:04,972 --> 01:33:08,071
The first flight stateside
left Guantanamo Bay at 2300.

1548
01:33:08,141 --> 01:33:11,915
It arrived at Andrews Air Force Base
at a few minutes past 2:00.

1549
01:33:11,980 --> 01:33:15,047
Really? Then why isn't it
listed in the tower chief’s log?

1550
01:33:17,069 --> 01:33:18,312
Jessup.

1551
01:33:18,380 --> 01:33:20,716
What are you telling me?
He fixed the logbook?

1552
01:33:22,670 --> 01:33:26,532
Maybe he can make it so a plane didn't
take off, but I can prove one landed.

1553
01:33:26,605 --> 01:33:28,612
I'll get the logbook from Andrews.

1554
01:33:28,685 --> 01:33:31,533
You're not gonna find anything
in the Andrews logbook, either.

1555
01:33:31,599 --> 01:33:33,453
He can make
an entire flight disappear?

1556
01:33:33,518 --> 01:33:37,829
Jessup is about to be appointed director
of operations for the Security Council.

1557
01:33:37,903 --> 01:33:41,733
You don't get to that position without
knowing how to sidestep some land mines.

1558
01:33:41,807 --> 01:33:44,557
He's not gonna be able
to sidestep you.

1559
01:33:44,624 --> 01:33:46,926
You don't still intend
to put me on the stand?

1560
01:33:46,992 --> 01:33:49,806
Thursday morning, 10:00.

1561
01:33:54,064 --> 01:33:57,741
There's gotta be someone
who can testify to the flight.

1562
01:33:57,809 --> 01:34:00,908
This isn't TWA.
There isn't a regular flight schedule.

1563
01:34:00,977 --> 01:34:03,660
Do you have any idea how many planes
take off and land every day?

1564
01:34:03,729 --> 01:34:07,025
A ground crew kid won't remember
a flight that landed four weeks ago.

1565
01:34:07,089 --> 01:34:10,122
- How do you know if you don't check?
- Forget the flight!

1566
01:34:10,193 --> 01:34:13,838
Markinson will testify that Jessup
refused to transfer Santiago.

1567
01:34:13,906 --> 01:34:16,361
He'll testify to the forged transfer,
and that'll be enough.

1568
01:34:16,434 --> 01:34:18,856
That and Downey's testimony
really ought to be enough.

1569
01:34:24,147 --> 01:34:27,944
Why did you go into Santiago's room
on the night of the 6th?

1570
01:34:28,018 --> 01:34:31,118
To give Private Santiago
a Code Red, ma'am.

1571
01:34:31,187 --> 01:34:33,292
Why did you give him a Code Red?

1572
01:34:33,363 --> 01:34:36,659
I was ordered to give him a Code Red
by the platoon commander...

1573
01:34:36,725 --> 01:34:40,783
of Rifle Security Company Windward,
Lieutenant Jonathan James Kendrick.

1574
01:34:41,939 --> 01:34:44,242
You're gonna do fine.

1575
01:34:45,780 --> 01:34:48,169
You think they'll let us go back
to our platoon soon, ma'am?

1576
01:34:49,556 --> 01:34:51,379
Absolutely.

1577
01:34:54,454 --> 01:34:56,788
Do you remember the order of questions?
Are you sure?

1578
01:34:56,853 --> 01:34:59,668
And we'll use small words, 'cause he
gets rattled if he doesn't understand.

1579
01:34:59,734 --> 01:35:02,516
- I'm just saying go slow.
- I'm gonna go slow.

1580
01:35:02,582 --> 01:35:05,396
And get him off
as fast as you can.

1581
01:35:05,461 --> 01:35:08,277
What?
It's gonna be fine.

1582
01:35:10,614 --> 01:35:12,502
Dear Mr. and Mrs. Santiago...

1583
01:35:13,783 --> 01:35:16,150
I was William's executive officer.

1584
01:35:16,215 --> 01:35:19,564
I knew your son vaguely,
which is to say I knew his name.

1585
01:35:20,598 --> 01:35:22,509
In a matter of time,
the trial of the two men...

1586
01:35:22,583 --> 01:35:25,169
charged with your son's death
will be concluded...

1587
01:35:25,240 --> 01:35:27,411
and seven men and two women
whom you've never met...

1588
01:35:27,479 --> 01:35:31,310
will try to offer you an explanation
as to why William is dead.

1589
01:35:31,385 --> 01:35:34,865
For my part, I've done as much as I can
to bring the truth to light.

1590
01:35:35,704 --> 01:35:37,166
And the truth is this--

1591
01:35:37,241 --> 01:35:39,696
Your son is dead for only one reason--

1592
01:35:39,769 --> 01:35:42,583
I wasn't strong enough to stop it.

1593
01:35:42,648 --> 01:35:46,872
Always, Lieutenant Colonel
Matthew Andrew Markinson...

1594
01:35:46,937 --> 01:35:48,366
United States Marine Corps.

1595
01:35:53,306 --> 01:35:56,688
Private, I want you
to tell us one last time.

1596
01:35:56,762 --> 01:36:02,360
Why did you go to Private Santiago's
room on the night of September 6?

1597
01:36:02,427 --> 01:36:04,728
A Code Red was ordered
by my platoon commander...

1598
01:36:04,794 --> 01:36:07,032
Lieutenant Jonathan James Kendrick.

1599
01:36:07,580 --> 01:36:09,271
Thank you.

1600
01:36:09,340 --> 01:36:10,867
Your witness.

1601
01:36:15,228 --> 01:36:17,333
Private, the week of2 September...

1602
01:36:17,404 --> 01:36:20,753
the switch log has you down
at Post 39 until 1600.

1603
01:36:20,828 --> 01:36:21,973
Is that correct?

1604
01:36:22,044 --> 01:36:24,859
I'm sure it is, sir.
They keep that log pretty good.

1605
01:36:24,924 --> 01:36:28,373
How far is it from Post 39
to the Windward Barracks?

1606
01:36:28,446 --> 01:36:31,762
Well, it's a ways, sir.
It's a hike.

1607
01:36:31,838 --> 01:36:34,554
About how far by Jeep?

1608
01:36:34,621 --> 01:36:37,850
About ten or fifteen minutes, sir.

1609
01:36:37,917 --> 01:36:39,739
You ever had to walk it?

1610
01:36:39,806 --> 01:36:43,483
Yes, sir. That day, Friday.
The pickup private--

1611
01:36:43,550 --> 01:36:46,486
That's what we call the guy
who drops us off and picks us up...

1612
01:36:46,559 --> 01:36:49,624
also 'cause he can get girls
in New York City.

1613
01:36:50,624 --> 01:36:52,696
The pickup private got a flat,
sir, right at 39.

1614
01:36:52,767 --> 01:36:55,483
He pulled up and, bam,
blowout with no spare.

1615
01:36:55,551 --> 01:36:57,525
So we had to double-time it
back to the barracks.

1616
01:36:57,599 --> 01:37:01,145
And if it’s about ten or fifteen
minutes by Jeep, I'm guessing...

1617
01:37:01,215 --> 01:37:04,150
it must be a good hour by foot,
am I right?

1618
01:37:04,224 --> 01:37:07,192
Pickup and me did it
in 45 flat, sir.

1619
01:37:07,264 --> 01:37:08,638
Not bad.

1620
01:37:10,016 --> 01:37:13,312
You've said that your assault
on Private Santiago...

1621
01:37:13,378 --> 01:37:16,508
was a result of a order
that Lieutenant Kendrick gave you...

1622
01:37:16,577 --> 01:37:19,991
in your barracks room
at 1620, am I right?

1623
01:37:21,089 --> 01:37:22,617
Yes, sir.

1624
01:37:22,690 --> 01:37:26,334
But you just said that you didn't
make it back to the barracks until 1645.

1625
01:37:28,802 --> 01:37:32,763
Well, if you didn't make it back
to the barracks until 1645...

1626
01:37:32,834 --> 01:37:34,938
how could you be
in your room at 1620?

1627
01:37:35,939 --> 01:37:38,622
Well, you see, sir,
there was a blowout--

1628
01:37:38,691 --> 01:37:42,434
Did you ever actually hear
Lieutenant Kendrick order a Code Red?

1629
01:37:42,500 --> 01:37:44,158
Well, Hal said that--

1630
01:37:44,228 --> 01:37:46,649
Private, did you ever
actually hear...

1631
01:37:46,724 --> 01:37:49,342
Lieutenant Kendrick
order a Code Red?

1632
01:37:51,044 --> 01:37:54,240
I'd like to request a recess
in order to confer with my client.

1633
01:37:54,307 --> 01:37:56,544
- Why did you go into Santiago's room?
- The witness has rights!

1634
01:37:56,612 --> 01:37:59,745
- The witness has been read his rights.
- The question will be repeated.

1635
01:37:59,814 --> 01:38:01,668
Why did you go
into Santiago's room?

1636
01:38:01,733 --> 01:38:05,029
Did Lance Corporal Dawson tell you
to give Santiago a Code Red?

1637
01:38:05,094 --> 01:38:06,784
- Don't look at him!
- Hal!

1638
01:38:06,853 --> 01:38:08,708
Answer the captain's question!

1639
01:38:11,877 --> 01:38:14,114
Yes, Captain, I was given an order
by my squad leader...

1640
01:38:14,182 --> 01:38:17,378
Lance Corporal Harold W. Dawson,
United States Marine Corps...

1641
01:38:17,446 --> 01:38:18,657
and I followed it.

1642
01:38:39,208 --> 01:38:40,801
Where do you think he is?

1643
01:38:42,985 --> 01:38:45,635
As far as Downey was concerned,
it was an order from Kendrick.

1644
01:38:45,704 --> 01:38:47,591
It doesn't matter that
he didn't hear it firsthand.

1645
01:38:47,656 --> 01:38:50,592
He doesn't distinguish
between the two.

1646
01:38:54,600 --> 01:38:56,805
Danny, I'm sorry.

1647
01:38:57,674 --> 01:38:59,168
Don't worry about it.

1648
01:38:59,242 --> 01:39:01,696
Sam and I were just talking about
how all we really have to do...

1649
01:39:01,769 --> 01:39:04,520
is call some witnesses
who will talk about implied orders.

1650
01:39:04,587 --> 01:39:07,042
Maybe we can put Downey back
on the stand before we get to Dawson.

1651
01:39:07,786 --> 01:39:12,227
If we work at it, we can get Dawson
charged with the Kennedy assassination.

1652
01:39:15,404 --> 01:39:16,516
Are you drunk?

1653
01:39:17,355 --> 01:39:20,007
Pretty much.

1654
01:39:20,076 --> 01:39:22,312
Yeah.

1655
01:39:22,380 --> 01:39:25,795
I'll put on a pot of coffee.
We've got a long night's work ahead.

1656
01:39:26,892 --> 01:39:29,193
She's gonna make coffee.

1657
01:39:30,284 --> 01:39:32,171
That's nice.

1658
01:39:35,949 --> 01:39:38,666
Downey wasn’t in his room.

1659
01:39:38,733 --> 01:39:40,555
Wasn't even there.

1660
01:39:41,934 --> 01:39:45,000
That was an important piece
of information, don’t you think?

1661
01:39:47,373 --> 01:39:51,499
Danny, it was a setback,
and I'm sorry.

1662
01:39:51,567 --> 01:39:54,152
But we fix it,
and move on to Markinson.

1663
01:39:55,822 --> 01:39:57,481
Markinson's dead.

1664
01:40:03,118 --> 01:40:06,981
You really gotta hand it
to those Federal Marshals, boy.

1665
01:40:07,055 --> 01:40:09,607
It's not like he hanged himself
by his shoelaces...

1666
01:40:09,679 --> 01:40:12,200
or slashed his wrists
with a concealed butter knife.

1667
01:40:12,272 --> 01:40:13,646
This guy...

1668
01:40:15,504 --> 01:40:19,017
got into full dress uniform,
stood in the middle of that room...

1669
01:40:19,088 --> 01:40:22,122
drew a nickel-plated pistol
from his holster...

1670
01:40:22,192 --> 01:40:24,494
and fired a bullet into his mouth.

1671
01:40:28,241 --> 01:40:31,951
Anyway, since we seem to be out of
witnesses, I thought I'd drink a little.

1672
01:40:32,017 --> 01:40:34,123
I still think we can win.

1673
01:40:36,082 --> 01:40:37,642
Maybe you should drink a little.

1674
01:40:37,714 --> 01:40:42,504
We'll go to Randolph in the morning and
make a motion for a 24-hour continuance.

1675
01:40:42,578 --> 01:40:45,709
- Why would we want to do that?
- To subpoena Colonel Jessup.

1676
01:40:46,834 --> 01:40:49,486
- What?
- Listen for a second. Hear me out.

1677
01:40:49,555 --> 01:40:51,497
I won't listen,
and I won't hear you out.

1678
01:40:51,571 --> 01:40:53,774
Your passion is compelling, Jo.
It's also useless.

1679
01:40:53,843 --> 01:40:56,843
Louden Downey
needed a trial lawyer today.

1680
01:40:59,731 --> 01:41:01,357
You're chicken shit.

1681
01:41:01,427 --> 01:41:04,046
You're gonna use what happened today
as an excuse to give up.

1682
01:41:05,460 --> 01:41:06,988
It's over.

1683
01:41:07,061 --> 01:41:09,516
Why did you ask Jessup
for the transfer order?

1684
01:41:09,589 --> 01:41:12,110
- In Cuba. Why?
- What does it matter?

1685
01:41:12,182 --> 01:41:14,734
- I wanted the damn transfer order!
- Bullshit.

1686
01:41:14,805 --> 01:41:18,154
You could've gotten it by calling
any department at the Pentagon.

1687
01:41:18,229 --> 01:41:22,768
You didn't want the transfer order.
You wanted to see Jessup’s reaction.

1688
01:41:22,837 --> 01:41:25,773
You had an instinct,
and it was confirmed by Markinson.

1689
01:41:25,846 --> 01:41:28,661
Let's put Jessup on the stand
and end this thing!

1690
01:41:28,726 --> 01:41:32,719
What possible good could come
from putting Jessup on the stand?

1691
01:41:32,790 --> 01:41:34,831
He told Kendrick
to order the Code Red.

1692
01:41:34,903 --> 01:41:38,797
He did? That's great!
Why didn’t you say so?

1693
01:41:38,870 --> 01:41:41,042
And of course
you have proof of that!

1694
01:41:41,111 --> 01:41:45,170
Oh, I'm sorry. I forgot. You were sick
the day they taught law at law school.

1695
01:41:45,239 --> 01:41:47,606
You put him on the stand,
and you get it from him.

1696
01:41:47,671 --> 01:41:51,534
Oh, we get it from him!
Yes! No problem!

1697
01:41:51,608 --> 01:41:55,284
Colonel Jessup, isn't it true that
you ordered the Code Red on Santiago?

1698
01:41:55,351 --> 01:41:58,352
- Listen, we're all a little--
- I'm sorry. Your time's run out.

1699
01:41:58,424 --> 01:42:01,391
What do we have for the losers?
Well, for our defendants...

1700
01:42:01,465 --> 01:42:03,735
it's a lifetime
at exotic Fort Leavenworth.

1701
01:42:03,802 --> 01:42:06,649
And for Defense Counsel Kaffee...

1702
01:42:06,713 --> 01:42:08,436
it's a court-martial!

1703
01:42:08,505 --> 01:42:11,539
Yes, Johnny,
after falsely accusing...

1704
01:42:11,609 --> 01:42:13,846
a highly decorated Marine officer...

1705
01:42:13,914 --> 01:42:15,702
of conspiracy and perjury...

1706
01:42:15,769 --> 01:42:18,770
Lieutenant Kaffee will have
a long and prosperous career...

1707
01:42:18,842 --> 01:42:23,861
teaching typewriter maintenance
at the Rocco Clubo School for Women.

1708
01:42:23,931 --> 01:42:26,866
Thank you for playing
'Should we or should we not...

1709
01:42:26,939 --> 01:42:29,874
follow the advice
of the galactic ally stupid?'

1710
01:42:50,845 --> 01:42:53,779
I'm sorry I lost
your set of steak knives.

1711
01:43:10,077 --> 01:43:11,933
Stop cleaning up.

1712
01:43:16,927 --> 01:43:18,783
Stop cleaning up.

1713
01:43:26,944 --> 01:43:29,759
- Want a drink?
- Yeah.

1714
01:43:47,041 --> 01:43:50,140
- Is your father proud of you?
- Don't do this to yourself.

1715
01:43:50,209 --> 01:43:51,867
I'll bet he is.

1716
01:43:52,641 --> 01:43:55,840
I'll bet he bores the shit
out of the neighbors and relatives.

1717
01:43:55,907 --> 01:44:00,184
'Sam's made Law Review.
He's got a big case he's making.

1718
01:44:00,258 --> 01:44:03,259
He's arguing.
He's making an argument.'

1719
01:44:08,546 --> 01:44:12,607
I think my father would’ve enjoyed
seeing me graduate from law school.

1720
01:44:15,972 --> 01:44:18,558
I think he would've liked that
an awful lot.

1721
01:44:21,028 --> 01:44:23,875
Did I ever tell you I wrote a paper
about your father in college?

1722
01:44:24,901 --> 01:44:26,276
Yeah?

1723
01:44:26,341 --> 01:44:28,828
One of the best
trial lawyers ever.

1724
01:44:28,900 --> 01:44:32,097
Yes, he was.

1725
01:44:32,165 --> 01:44:34,370
If were Dawson and Downey
and I had a choice...

1726
01:44:34,438 --> 01:44:37,285
between you or your father
to represent me in this case...

1727
01:44:37,349 --> 01:44:40,220
I'd choose you any day of the week
and twice on Sunday.

1728
01:44:40,294 --> 01:44:43,556
You should've seen yourself
thunder away at Kendrick.

1729
01:44:46,534 --> 01:44:48,390
Would you put Jessup on the stand?

1730
01:44:51,975 --> 01:44:56,253
- Do you think my father would have?
- With the evidence we got?

1731
01:44:56,328 --> 01:44:59,110
Not in a million years.

1732
01:44:59,175 --> 01:45:02,405
But here's the thing-- and there's
really know way of getting around this--

1733
01:45:02,472 --> 01:45:06,628
Neither Lyle Kaffee nor Sam Weinberg
are lead counsel for the defense...

1734
01:45:06,696 --> 01:45:09,698
in the matter of
U.S. v. Dawson and Downey.

1735
01:45:09,770 --> 01:45:13,544
So there's really only one question--
What would you do?

1736
01:45:25,097 --> 01:45:28,993
Jo, get in the car.
Joanne, please get in the car.

1737
01:45:29,067 --> 01:45:30,441
Look--

1738
01:45:33,771 --> 01:45:37,927
I apologize. I was angry.
I'm sorry about what I said.

1739
01:45:37,994 --> 01:45:40,483
I'm gonna put Jessup on the stand.

1740
01:45:59,916 --> 01:46:01,509
What do you suggest we do?

1741
01:46:01,580 --> 01:46:03,686
I say we hit Jessup
with the phony transfer order.

1742
01:46:03,757 --> 01:46:05,612
What's a transfer order
without a witness?

1743
01:46:05,677 --> 01:46:07,204
- We have a witness.
- A dead witness.

1744
01:46:07,278 --> 01:46:10,061
In the hands of a lesser attorney,
that would be a problem.

1745
01:46:10,126 --> 01:46:12,492
Look at this. Last night
he's swimming in Jack Daniels...

1746
01:46:12,558 --> 01:46:15,176
and now he can leap tall buildings
in a single bound.

1747
01:46:15,246 --> 01:46:18,312
I'm getting my second wind.
Sit down, both of you.

1748
01:46:18,382 --> 01:46:22,725
Good. Jessup told Kendrick
to order the Code Red. Kendrick did.

1749
01:46:22,798 --> 01:46:24,938
Our clients followed the order.
The cover-up isn't our case.

1750
01:46:25,008 --> 01:46:29,448
To win, Jessup needs to tell the court
members that he ordered the Code Red.

1751
01:46:29,519 --> 01:46:33,097
- You think you can get him to say it?
- I think he wants to say it.

1752
01:46:33,167 --> 01:46:35,338
I think he's pissed off
that he's got to hide from us.

1753
01:46:35,408 --> 01:46:38,756
I think he wants to say that he made
a command decision, and that's the end.

1754
01:46:38,831 --> 01:46:41,647
He eats breakfast 300 yards away...

1755
01:46:41,713 --> 01:46:44,876
from 4,000 Cubans
that are trained to kill him.

1756
01:46:44,944 --> 01:46:46,920
No one's gonna tell him
how to run his unit.

1757
01:46:46,994 --> 01:46:49,743
Least of all the Harvard mouth
in his faggoty white uniform.

1758
01:46:49,809 --> 01:46:51,849
I need to shake him,
put him on the defensive...

1759
01:46:51,921 --> 01:46:54,507
and lead him right
where he's dying to go.

1760
01:46:54,578 --> 01:46:57,425
- That's it? That's the plan?
- That's the plan.

1761
01:46:57,489 --> 01:47:00,556
- How are you gonna do it?
- I have no idea.

1762
01:47:00,626 --> 01:47:02,667
- I need my bat.
- Your what?

1763
01:47:02,739 --> 01:47:04,910
I think better with my bat.
Where's my bat?

1764
01:47:04,979 --> 01:47:08,295
- I put it in the closet.
- You put it in the closet?

1765
01:47:08,370 --> 01:47:12,113
- I was tripping on it.
- Don't ever put that bat in the closet.

1766
01:47:12,178 --> 01:47:15,822
- He thinks better with his bat?
- I can understand that.

1767
01:47:26,804 --> 01:47:29,586
Stay here.
I'm going to the office for a while.

1768
01:47:32,021 --> 01:47:34,541
He does think better with that bat.

1769
01:47:56,119 --> 01:47:59,315
Sam, I need you
to do something for me.

1770
01:48:02,392 --> 01:48:05,490
- What's going on?
- Gotta go out to Andrews.

1771
01:48:28,376 --> 01:48:30,231
- Where's Sam?
- He's on his way.

1772
01:48:30,296 --> 01:48:32,152
- Did he get the guys?
- Yeah.

1773
01:48:32,217 --> 01:48:35,087
Listen, can I talk to you
for a second?

1774
01:48:35,162 --> 01:48:37,300
Oh, yeah, sure.

1775
01:48:47,322 --> 01:48:48,915
How you feeling?

1776
01:48:50,266 --> 01:48:53,683
Well, I think Jessup’s
gonna have his hands full today.

1777
01:48:56,315 --> 01:48:58,170
Listen, Danny...

1778
01:48:59,291 --> 01:49:01,626
when you're out there today...

1779
01:49:01,692 --> 01:49:04,725
if you feel like
it's not gonna happen...

1780
01:49:04,796 --> 01:49:07,796
if you feel like
he's not gonna say it...

1781
01:49:07,868 --> 01:49:09,395
don't go for it.

1782
01:49:10,845 --> 01:49:12,984
You could get in trouble.

1783
01:49:13,053 --> 01:49:15,060
I'm special counsel
for Internal Affairs...

1784
01:49:15,133 --> 01:49:17,589
and I'm telling you
you could get in a lot of trouble.

1785
01:49:17,662 --> 01:49:19,571
Wait, Lieutenant Commander Galloway...

1786
01:49:19,646 --> 01:49:23,705
you're not suggesting
that I back off a material witness?

1787
01:49:23,774 --> 01:49:26,840
If you think you can't get him, yeah.

1788
01:49:28,991 --> 01:49:30,584
All rise.

1789
01:49:35,230 --> 01:49:38,101
- Where's Sam?
- He's on his way.

1790
01:49:43,487 --> 01:49:45,975
- Call your first witness.
- Where is he?

1791
01:49:46,047 --> 01:49:48,285
- He'll be here.
- Lieutenant.

1792
01:49:48,353 --> 01:49:49,946
Call your witness.

1793
01:49:56,352 --> 01:49:58,905
Defense calls Colonel Nathan Jessup.

1794
01:50:15,010 --> 01:50:17,727
Colonel Jessup, would you raise
your right hand please, sir?

1795
01:50:17,794 --> 01:50:21,110
Do you solemnly swear that the testimony
you will give in this court-martial...

1796
01:50:21,186 --> 01:50:24,483
will be the truth, the whole truth
and nothing but the truth?

1797
01:50:24,547 --> 01:50:25,889
Yes, I do.

1798
01:50:25,955 --> 01:50:27,362
Have a seat please, sir.

1799
01:50:28,931 --> 01:50:32,248
Would you state your name, rank
and current billet for the record, sir?

1800
01:50:32,323 --> 01:50:35,323
Colonel Nathan R. Jessup,
commanding officer...

1801
01:50:35,396 --> 01:50:38,560
Marine Ground Forces,
Guantanamo Bay, Cuba.

1802
01:50:38,628 --> 01:50:40,865
- Thank you, sir.
- He's not here.

1803
01:50:46,437 --> 01:50:49,852
Colonel, when you learned
of Santiago’s letter to the N.I.S....

1804
01:50:49,925 --> 01:50:52,925
you had a meeting
with your two senior officers.

1805
01:50:52,997 --> 01:50:54,972
- Is that right?
- Yes.

1806
01:50:55,046 --> 01:50:58,493
The platoon commander,
Lieutenant Jonathan Kendrick...

1807
01:50:58,565 --> 01:51:02,080
and the executive officer,
Lieutenant Colonel Matthew Markinson.

1808
01:51:02,151 --> 01:51:03,612
Yes.

1809
01:51:03,687 --> 01:51:07,997
And at present Colonel Markinson
is dead. Is that right?

1810
01:51:08,071 --> 01:51:11,965
Objection. I'd like to know just what
the defense counsel is implying.

1811
01:51:12,038 --> 01:51:15,334
I'm implying simply that at present
Colonel Markinson is not alive.

1812
01:51:15,399 --> 01:51:18,977
Colonel Jessup doesn't need to appear
in court to confirm that information.

1813
01:51:19,047 --> 01:51:21,382
I just wasn't sure the witness was aware
that two days ago...

1814
01:51:21,447 --> 01:51:24,132
the colonel took his own life
with a .45-caliber pistol.

1815
01:51:24,201 --> 01:51:26,567
The witness is aware,
the court is aware...

1816
01:51:26,632 --> 01:51:28,487
and now the court members
are aware.

1817
01:51:28,552 --> 01:51:31,968
We thank you for bringing this
to our attention.

1818
01:51:32,041 --> 01:51:33,699
Move on, Lieutenant..

1819
01:51:33,768 --> 01:51:35,459
Yes, sir.

1820
01:51:35,529 --> 01:51:39,011
Colonel, you gave Lieutenant Kendrick
an order at this meeting, right?

1821
01:51:39,082 --> 01:51:43,238
I told Kendrick to tell his men
that Santiago wasn't to be touched.

1822
01:51:43,306 --> 01:51:46,121
And did you give an order
to Colonel Markinson as well?

1823
01:51:46,186 --> 01:51:51,488
I ordered Markinson to have Santiago
transferred off the base immediately.

1824
01:51:51,561 --> 01:51:53,285
Why?

1825
01:51:53,355 --> 01:51:56,966
I felt his life might be in danger
once word of the letter got out.

1826
01:51:57,034 --> 01:51:58,409
Grave danger?

1827
01:51:58,474 --> 01:52:00,580
Is there another kind?

1828
01:52:04,043 --> 01:52:07,818
Colonel, we have the transfer order
that you and Markinson co-signed...

1829
01:52:07,884 --> 01:52:12,323
ordering that Santiago be on a flight
leaving Guantanamo at 6:00 the next day.

1830
01:52:12,395 --> 01:52:17,285
- Was that the first flight?
- The 0600 was the first flight.

1831
01:52:21,005 --> 01:52:24,235
You flew up to Washington this morning.
Is that right?

1832
01:52:24,301 --> 01:52:27,562
I notice you’re wearing your
class 'A' dress uniform in court today.

1833
01:52:27,628 --> 01:52:30,695
- As are you, Lieutenant.
- Did you wear that on the plane?

1834
01:52:30,765 --> 01:52:33,448
Please the court, is this dialogue
relevant to anything--

1835
01:52:33,517 --> 01:52:36,103
Defense didn't have the opportunity
to depose this witness.

1836
01:52:36,173 --> 01:52:39,720
- I'd ask for a little latitude.
- A very little latitude.

1837
01:52:41,871 --> 01:52:43,812
I wore utilities on the plane.

1838
01:52:43,886 --> 01:52:46,822
- You brought your dress uniform?
- Yes.

1839
01:52:46,895 --> 01:52:50,156
- Toothbrush, shaving kit, underwear?
- Your Honor!

1840
01:52:50,222 --> 01:52:52,492
Is the colonel's underwear
a matter of national security?

1841
01:52:52,559 --> 01:52:55,821
Gentlemen! You better get somewhere
fast with this, Lieutenant.

1842
01:52:55,888 --> 01:52:57,862
Yes, sir. Colonel?

1843
01:52:58,927 --> 01:53:02,506
I brought a change of clothes
and some personal items.

1844
01:53:02,576 --> 01:53:04,365
Thank you.

1845
01:53:04,432 --> 01:53:07,945
After Dawson and Downey's arrest
on the night of the sixth...

1846
01:53:08,016 --> 01:53:12,108
Santiago's barracks were sealed off
and its contents inventoried.

1847
01:53:12,177 --> 01:53:15,342
' Four pairs camouflage pants,
three long-sleeve khaki shirts...

1848
01:53:15,410 --> 01:53:19,152
three pairs of boots, four pairs
green socks, three green T-shirts--'

1849
01:53:19,218 --> 01:53:22,033
Please the court, is there a question
anywhere in our future?

1850
01:53:22,098 --> 01:53:25,098
Lieutenant Kaffee, I have to ask you
to state your question.

1851
01:53:25,170 --> 01:53:27,853
I'm wondering why Santiago
wasn't packed.

1852
01:53:29,842 --> 01:53:32,974
I'll tell you what.
We'll get back to that one in a minute.

1853
01:53:33,843 --> 01:53:37,040
This is a record of all phone calls made
from your base in the past 24 hours.

1854
01:53:37,107 --> 01:53:40,554
After being subpoenaed to Washington,
you made three calls.

1855
01:53:40,627 --> 01:53:42,864
Do you recognize
those number, sir?

1856
01:53:42,931 --> 01:53:45,931
I called Colonel Fitzhughes
in Quantico, Virginia.

1857
01:53:46,003 --> 01:53:48,686
I wanted to let him know
that I would be in town.

1858
01:53:48,755 --> 01:53:52,172
The second call was to arrange a meeting
with Congressman Richmond...

1859
01:53:52,245 --> 01:53:54,416
of the House Armed Services Committee.

1860
01:53:54,485 --> 01:53:57,419
And the third call
was to my sister Elizabeth.

1861
01:53:57,492 --> 01:53:59,500
Why did you make that call, sir?

1862
01:53:59,573 --> 01:54:02,835
I thought she might like
to have dinner tonight.

1863
01:54:02,901 --> 01:54:06,130
- I'm gonna stop this.
- These are phone records from Gitmo...

1864
01:54:06,198 --> 01:54:10,257
for September 6,
and these are 14 letters...

1865
01:54:10,326 --> 01:54:12,944
that Santiago wrote in nine months...

1866
01:54:13,014 --> 01:54:16,048
requesting-- in fact, begging--
for a transfer.

1867
01:54:16,118 --> 01:54:19,184
Upon hearing the news that
he was finally getting his transfer...

1868
01:54:19,254 --> 01:54:23,051
Santiago was so excited that
do you know how many people he called?

1869
01:54:23,127 --> 01:54:25,494
Zero. Nobody.

1870
01:54:25,559 --> 01:54:29,270
Not one call to his parents
saying he was coming home.

1871
01:54:29,336 --> 01:54:32,434
Not one call to a friend, saying,
'Can you pick me up at the airport?'

1872
01:54:32,503 --> 01:54:36,181
He was asleep in his bed at midnight,
and according to you...

1873
01:54:36,248 --> 01:54:38,670
he was getting on a plane
in six hours.

1874
01:54:38,744 --> 01:54:42,159
Yet everything he owned
was hanging neatly in his closet...

1875
01:54:42,232 --> 01:54:44,753
and folded neatly in his footlocker.

1876
01:54:44,824 --> 01:54:48,436
You were leaving for one day.
You packed a bag and made three calls.

1877
01:54:48,505 --> 01:54:52,663
Santiago was leaving
for the rest of his life...

1878
01:54:54,362 --> 01:54:57,012
and he hadn't called a soul...

1879
01:54:57,081 --> 01:54:59,635
and he hadn't packed a thing.

1880
01:55:02,746 --> 01:55:04,437
Can you explain that?

1881
01:55:06,843 --> 01:55:09,014
The fact is,
there was no transfer order.

1882
01:55:09,083 --> 01:55:11,733
Santiago wasn't going anywhere.
Isn't that right, Colonel?

1883
01:55:11,802 --> 01:55:15,119
Objection. Your Honor, it's obvious
that Lieutenant Kaffee's intention...

1884
01:55:15,195 --> 01:55:17,431
is the smear
a high-ranking Marine officer...

1885
01:55:17,499 --> 01:55:21,013
in the hope that the mere appearance
of impropriety will win him points.

1886
01:55:21,084 --> 01:55:24,859
It's my recommendation, sir,
that Lieutenant Kaffee be reprimanded...

1887
01:55:24,924 --> 01:55:27,706
and the witness be excused
with the court's deepest apologies.

1888
01:55:29,469 --> 01:55:32,436
Overruled.
Your objection is noted.

1889
01:55:38,621 --> 01:55:40,377
Is this funny, sir?

1890
01:55:40,445 --> 01:55:43,643
No, it's not.
It's tragic.

1891
01:55:43,710 --> 01:55:46,296
- Do you have an answer?
- Absolutely.

1892
01:55:46,366 --> 01:55:50,010
My answer is,
I don't have the first damn clue.

1893
01:55:50,078 --> 01:55:53,690
Maybe he was an early riser
and liked to pack in the morning.

1894
01:55:53,758 --> 01:55:56,475
And maybe he didn't have any friends.

1895
01:55:56,542 --> 01:55:59,892
I'm an educated man, but I'm afraid
I can't speak intelligently...

1896
01:55:59,967 --> 01:56:03,480
about the travel habits
of William Santiago.

1897
01:56:03,551 --> 01:56:08,373
What I do know is that he was set
to leave the base at 0600.

1898
01:56:09,215 --> 01:56:14,104
Now, are these really the questions
that I was called here to answer?

1899
01:56:14,176 --> 01:56:16,445
Phone calls and footlockers?

1900
01:56:16,512 --> 01:56:20,058
Please tell me that you have
something more, Lieutenant.

1901
01:56:20,128 --> 01:56:23,741
These two Marines
are on trial for their lives.

1902
01:56:23,809 --> 01:56:28,064
Please tell me that their lawyer hasn't
pinned their hopes to a phone bill.

1903
01:56:30,466 --> 01:56:33,761
Do you have any other questions
for me, counselor?

1904
01:56:51,748 --> 01:56:55,130
Lieutenant, do you have anything
further for this witness?

1905
01:57:02,340 --> 01:57:04,511
Thanks, Danny.
I love Washington.

1906
01:57:04,580 --> 01:57:07,069
Excuse me.
I didn't dismiss you.

1907
01:57:08,101 --> 01:57:09,791
I beg your pardon?

1908
01:57:09,860 --> 01:57:14,203
I'm not through with my examination.
Sit down.

1909
01:57:15,846 --> 01:57:18,496
- Colonel.
- What's that?

1910
01:57:18,566 --> 01:57:21,119
I'd appreciate it if you’d address me
as 'colonel' or 'sir.'

1911
01:57:21,190 --> 01:57:22,717
I believe I've earned it.

1912
01:57:22,790 --> 01:57:26,848
Defense counsel will address
the witness as 'colonel' or 'sir.'

1913
01:57:26,918 --> 01:57:29,766
I don't know what the hell
kind of unit you're running here.

1914
01:57:29,830 --> 01:57:33,475
The witness will address this court
as 'judge' or 'your honor.'

1915
01:57:33,542 --> 01:57:38,082
I'm quite certain I've earned it.
Take your seat, Colonel.

1916
01:57:42,856 --> 01:57:46,784
What do you want to discuss now?
My favorite color?

1917
01:57:48,007 --> 01:57:50,593
Colonel, the 6:00 a.m. flight
was the first one off the base?

1918
01:57:50,664 --> 01:57:51,680
Yes.

1919
01:57:51,753 --> 01:57:53,727
There wasn't a flight
that left seven hours earlier...

1920
01:57:53,801 --> 01:57:56,037
and landed at Andrews Air Force Base
at 2:00 a.m.?

1921
01:57:56,105 --> 01:57:58,953
Lieutenant, I think
we've covered this, haven't we?

1922
01:57:59,945 --> 01:58:01,985
Your Honor, these are
the tower chief’s logs...

1923
01:58:02,057 --> 01:58:04,774
for both Guantanamo Bay
and Andrews Air Force Base.

1924
01:58:04,842 --> 01:58:08,070
The Guantanamo log lists no flight
that left at 11:00 p.m.

1925
01:58:08,137 --> 01:58:10,626
The Andrews log lists no flight
that landed at 2:00 a.m.

1926
01:58:10,698 --> 01:58:13,186
I'd like to admit them
as defense exhibits Alpha and Bravo.

1927
01:58:13,930 --> 01:58:17,313
I don't understand. You're admitting
evidence of a flight that never existed.

1928
01:58:17,386 --> 01:58:19,754
We believe it did, sir.

1929
01:58:19,819 --> 01:58:22,983
Defense will be calling Airmen
Cecil O'Malley and Anthony Rodriguez.

1930
01:58:23,051 --> 01:58:25,953
They were working the ground crew
at Andrews at 2:00 a.m. on the 7th.

1931
01:58:26,027 --> 01:58:28,744
- These men weren't on the list.
- Rebuttal witnesses, Your Honor...

1932
01:58:28,812 --> 01:58:32,968
called specifically to refute testimony
offered under direct examination.

1933
01:58:33,036 --> 01:58:35,884
- I'll allow the witnesses.
- This is ridiculous.

1934
01:58:35,948 --> 01:58:40,170
- Colonel, a moment ago--
- Check the tower logs, for God's sake!

1935
01:58:41,099 --> 01:58:43,205
We'll get to the airmen
in just a minute, sir.

1936
01:58:44,204 --> 01:58:46,059
A moment ago you said that
you ordered Lieutenant Kendrick...

1937
01:58:46,124 --> 01:58:49,988
to tell his men
that Santiago wasn't to be touched.

1938
01:58:50,062 --> 01:58:51,556
That's right.

1939
01:58:51,630 --> 01:58:54,247
And Lieutenant Kendrick was clear
on what you wanted?

1940
01:58:54,317 --> 01:58:56,041
Crystal.

1941
01:58:56,109 --> 01:58:59,109
Any chance Lieutenant Kendrick
ignored the order?

1942
01:58:59,182 --> 01:59:01,091
Ignored the order?

1943
01:59:01,165 --> 01:59:04,132
Any chance he forgot about it?

1944
01:59:04,206 --> 01:59:08,168
Any chance Lieutenant Kendrick left your
office and said, 'The old man is wrong'?

1945
01:59:10,127 --> 01:59:12,299
When Lieutenant Kendrick
spoke to the platoon...

1946
01:59:12,368 --> 01:59:15,499
and ordered them not to touch Santiago,
any chance they ignored him?

1947
01:59:16,879 --> 01:59:19,749
You ever served
in an infantry unit, son?

1948
01:59:19,824 --> 01:59:22,987
- No, sir.
- Ever served in a forward area?

1949
01:59:24,271 --> 01:59:27,175
Ever put your life
in another man's hands?

1950
01:59:27,249 --> 01:59:29,769
Asked him to put his life in yours?

1951
01:59:30,992 --> 01:59:32,880
We follow orders, son.

1952
01:59:32,944 --> 01:59:35,792
We follow orders, or people die.

1953
01:59:35,857 --> 01:59:38,890
It's that simple.
Are we clear?

1954
01:59:38,960 --> 01:59:40,716
Yes, sir.

1955
01:59:40,784 --> 01:59:42,443
Are we clear?

1956
01:59:42,513 --> 01:59:44,369
Crystal.

1957
01:59:46,418 --> 01:59:50,794
I have just one more question before
I call Airmen O'Malley and Rodriguez.

1958
01:59:52,083 --> 01:59:56,173
If you gave an order
that Santiago wasn't to be touched...

1959
01:59:56,242 --> 01:59:58,664
and your orders
are always followed...

1960
02:00:00,563 --> 02:00:03,531
then why would Santiago
be in danger?

1961
02:00:05,364 --> 02:00:08,942
Why would it be necessary
to transfer him off the base?

1962
02:00:14,324 --> 02:00:17,324
Santiago was a substandard Marine.

1963
02:00:17,396 --> 02:00:19,698
- He was being transferred--
- That's not what you said!

1964
02:00:19,765 --> 02:00:23,246
You said he was being transferred
because he was in grave danger.

1965
02:00:23,317 --> 02:00:26,133
I said, 'Grave danger?'
You said, 'Is there any other kind?'

1966
02:00:26,198 --> 02:00:28,620
- I recall what I said.
- I can have it read back to you.

1967
02:00:28,693 --> 02:00:31,562
I know what I said!
I don't have to have it read back to me.

1968
02:00:31,637 --> 02:00:35,086
Then why the two orders?
Colonel?

1969
02:00:36,950 --> 02:00:39,536
Sometimes men take matters
into their own hands.

1970
02:00:39,606 --> 02:00:42,574
You've made it clear that your men
never take matters into their own hands.

1971
02:00:42,647 --> 02:00:44,534
Your men follow orders,
or people die.

1972
02:00:44,598 --> 02:00:47,119
So Santiago should have been
in danger, should he?

1973
02:00:47,190 --> 02:00:50,901
- You snotty little bastard.
- I'd like to ask for a recess.

1974
02:00:50,967 --> 02:00:54,447
- I'd like an answer to the question.
- The court will wait for an answer.

1975
02:00:55,255 --> 02:00:57,492
If Lieutenant Kendrick
gave an order...

1976
02:00:57,560 --> 02:01:00,408
that Santiago
wasn't to be touched...

1977
02:01:00,472 --> 02:01:02,327
then why did he
have to be transferred?

1978
02:01:05,112 --> 02:01:09,138
Lieutenant Kendrick ordered the Code Red
because that's what you told him to do!

1979
02:01:09,208 --> 02:01:12,078
- Object!
- And then you cut these guys loose!

1980
02:01:12,153 --> 02:01:15,568
- I'll hold you in contempt.
- You doctored the logbook!

1981
02:01:15,641 --> 02:01:18,392
- Damn it, Kaffee!
- Consider yourself in contempt.

1982
02:01:18,458 --> 02:01:21,141
Colonel Jessup,
did you order the Code Red?

1983
02:01:21,210 --> 02:01:24,625
- You don't have to answer that.
- I'll answer the question.

1984
02:01:24,698 --> 02:01:26,641
- You want answers?
- I think I'm entitled!

1985
02:01:26,715 --> 02:01:29,016
- You want answers?
- I want the truth!

1986
02:01:29,082 --> 02:01:32,049
You can't handle the truth!

1987
02:01:32,122 --> 02:01:34,032
Son, we live in a world
that has walls...

1988
02:01:34,107 --> 02:01:36,628
and those walls have to be guarded
by men with guns.

1989
02:01:36,699 --> 02:01:40,890
Who's gonna do it? You?
You, Lieutenant Weinberg?

1990
02:01:40,956 --> 02:01:44,785
I have a greater responsibility
than you can possibly fathom.

1991
02:01:44,860 --> 02:01:48,177
You weep for Santiago,
and you curse the Marines.

1992
02:01:48,252 --> 02:01:51,929
You have the luxury
of not knowing what I know--

1993
02:01:51,996 --> 02:01:55,926
that Santiago's death,
while tragic, probably saved lives.

1994
02:01:55,997 --> 02:02:01,660
And my existence, while grotesque and
incomprehensible to you, saves lives!

1995
02:02:01,725 --> 02:02:05,686
You don't want the truth because
deep down you don't talk about...

1996
02:02:05,757 --> 02:02:07,829
you want me on that wall.

1997
02:02:07,901 --> 02:02:10,488
You need me on that wall!

1998
02:02:10,558 --> 02:02:15,031
We use words
like honor, code, loyalty.

1999
02:02:15,102 --> 02:02:18,648
We use these words as the backbone
of a life spent defending something.

2000
02:02:18,719 --> 02:02:20,629
You use them as a punch line.

2001
02:02:20,703 --> 02:02:24,380
I have neither the time
nor the inclination to explain myself...

2002
02:02:24,446 --> 02:02:28,440
to a man who rises and sleeps under
the blanket of the freedom I provide...

2003
02:02:28,511 --> 02:02:31,261
and then questions the manner
in which I provide it!

2004
02:02:31,327 --> 02:02:34,459
I would rather you just said thank you
and went on your way.

2005
02:02:34,528 --> 02:02:38,140
Otherwise, I suggest you
pick up a weapon and stand a post.

2006
02:02:38,208 --> 02:02:42,911
Either way, I don't give a damn
what you think you are entitled to!

2007
02:02:42,977 --> 02:02:44,570
Did you order the Code Red?

2008
02:02:44,641 --> 02:02:46,495
- I did the job--
- Did you order the Code Red?

2009
02:02:46,560 --> 02:02:48,798
You're goddamned right I did!

2010
02:02:59,394 --> 02:03:02,361
Please the court,
I suggest the members be dismissed...

2011
02:03:02,434 --> 02:03:05,533
so that we can move to an immediate
Article 39-A session.

2012
02:03:05,602 --> 02:03:07,936
The witness has rights.

2013
02:03:08,001 --> 02:03:10,142
Captain Ross?

2014
02:03:20,580 --> 02:03:24,093
The members of the court will retire
to an anteroom until further instructed.

2015
02:03:24,164 --> 02:03:25,888
All rise.

2016
02:03:27,077 --> 02:03:30,426
What the hell is this?
Colonel, what's going on?

2017
02:03:30,500 --> 02:03:32,923
I did my job.
I'd do it again.

2018
02:03:32,997 --> 02:03:35,997
I'm gonna get on a plane
and go on back to my base.

2019
02:03:36,069 --> 02:03:39,614
You're not going anywhere, Colonel.
M.P. s, guard the colonel.

2020
02:03:39,684 --> 02:03:41,059
Yes, sir.

2021
02:03:43,014 --> 02:03:45,435
- Captain Ross.
- What the hell is this?

2022
02:03:45,510 --> 02:03:48,293
Colonel Jessup, you have
the right to remain silent.

2023
02:03:48,359 --> 02:03:52,799
I'm being charged with a crime?
Is that what this is?

2024
02:03:52,871 --> 02:03:56,068
- I'm being charged with a crime?
- You have a right to consult a lawyer.

2025
02:03:56,135 --> 02:03:59,812
- This is funny. That's what this is.
- This lawyer may be appointed by you.

2026
02:03:59,879 --> 02:04:03,425
I'm gonna rip the eyes out of your head
and piss in your dead skull!

2027
02:04:03,495 --> 02:04:05,350
You fucked with the wrong Marine!

2028
02:04:05,416 --> 02:04:08,677
Colonel Jessup, do you understand
these rights as I have just read them?

2029
02:04:14,664 --> 02:04:17,315
You fucking people.

2030
02:04:17,384 --> 02:04:20,035
You have no idea
how to defend a nation.

2031
02:04:20,105 --> 02:04:23,401
All you did was weaken
a country today, Kaffee.

2032
02:04:23,465 --> 02:04:25,375
That's all you did.

2033
02:04:25,450 --> 02:04:30,338
You put people's lives in danger.
Sweet dreams, son.

2034
02:04:30,410 --> 02:04:32,483
Don't call me son.

2035
02:04:32,554 --> 02:04:36,809
I'm a lawyer and an officer
in the United States Navy...

2036
02:04:36,874 --> 02:04:39,525
and you're under arrest,
you son of a bitch.

2037
02:04:43,659 --> 02:04:45,546
The witness is excused.

2038
02:05:06,764 --> 02:05:07,779
All rise.

2039
02:05:18,830 --> 02:05:20,390
Have the members reached a verdict?

2040
02:05:20,462 --> 02:05:22,317
We have, sir.

2041
02:05:33,647 --> 02:05:36,963
Lance Corporal Dawson
and Private First Class Downey.

2042
02:05:40,208 --> 02:05:44,201
On the charge of murder,
the members find the accused...

2043
02:05:44,272 --> 02:05:46,126
not guilty.

2044
02:05:47,152 --> 02:05:50,600
On the charge
of conspiracy to commit murder...

2045
02:05:50,672 --> 02:05:54,284
the members find the accused
not guilty.

2046
02:05:56,977 --> 02:06:00,653
On the charge of conduct
unbecoming a United States Marine...

2047
02:06:00,721 --> 02:06:06,285
the members find the accused
guilty as charged.

2048
02:06:08,177 --> 02:06:11,211
The accused are hereby sentenced
to time already served...

2049
02:06:11,281 --> 02:06:15,952
and you are ordered to be dishonorably
discharged from the Marine Corps.

2050
02:06:17,299 --> 02:06:19,306
This court-martial is adjourned.

2051
02:06:19,379 --> 02:06:21,201
All rise.

2052
02:06:36,372 --> 02:06:38,260
What does that mean?

2053
02:06:43,220 --> 02:06:45,075
What did that mean?

2054
02:06:48,245 --> 02:06:52,272
I don't understand. Colonel Jessup
said he ordered the Code Red.

2055
02:06:52,342 --> 02:06:56,117
- I know.
- What did we do wrong?

2056
02:06:56,182 --> 02:06:59,565
- It's not that simple.
- We did nothing wrong!

2057
02:06:59,637 --> 02:07:00,979
Yeah, we did.

2058
02:07:03,990 --> 02:07:07,732
We were supposed to fight for people
who couldn't fight for themselves.

2059
02:07:08,823 --> 02:07:11,409
We were supposed
to fight for Willie.

2060
02:07:18,872 --> 02:07:21,774
I have to take these men
over to personnel for some paperwork.

2061
02:07:39,386 --> 02:07:41,971
You don't need to wear a patch
on your arm to have honor.

2062
02:07:48,315 --> 02:07:51,282
There's an officer on deck.

2063
